title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Let ice cream and Cool Whip set out to soften.
Crush cookies. Mix it all together and put in pan.
Freeze at least 3 hours.

title: lush cake
directions: Combine flour, oleo and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and let cool.

title: spaghetti squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place squash halves, cut side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and add boiling water to pan to a depth of 1 1/2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tender.
Remove from oven; let cool slightly. Using a fork, remove spaghetti-like strands of squash.
Combine squash, butter, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Toss until coated. Transfer to a serving plater and garnish, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: after-school applesauce cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, applesauce and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients, raisins and walnuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Drizzle glaze over warm cookies with spoon, then transfer to cooling rack.

title: ground beef teriyaki
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onions, celery, carrot and pepper until tender-crisp, stirring often.
Remove veggies to bowl.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.

title: frosted apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup of liquid.
Fold pineapple and bananas into gelatin mixture.
Pour into lightly oiled 9-inch square dish.
Chill until set.
Combine sugar, pineapple juice, flour, butter and egg in pan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Chill.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over salad.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Top with nuts.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine milk and soup; heat through.
Add cheese; heat until melted.
Stir often; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cheese, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate after melting in double boiler.
Add nuts.
Spread in 8-inch pan.
Chill for several hours.
Cut in squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: master baking mix
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat together in bowl egg, milk and sugar.
Add Master Mix.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans and bake 20 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix Oreos and margarine; spread in bottom of dish and freeze. Soften ice cream; beat with mixer and pour over Oreo crust. Freeze.
Combine chocolate, sugar, margarine and milk.
Cook 4 or 5 minutes until sugar and chocolate are dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator.
Pour over ice cream and freeze.

title: ultra easy pork chops
directions: Put tomato rice soup and water in baking pan. Add pork chops, with onion and green peppers slices on top.
Cover and Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 1\2 hour more.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Brown meat slightly in skillet.
Season with onion salt, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in this order: cheese, celery, olives, noodles, tomatoes and water.
Rinse out tomato can with 1/3 cup water and pour over all.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; cover.
Cook on high until steaming, then lower or simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: low-fat soup
directions: In a large pot, start beef broth. Add vegetables that you like and season as you like. Add water as you go to cover vegetables. Beef may be added to make this a beef stew or chicken stew.
Cook until carrots are soft as they require the most time, 30 to 45 minutes. Freezes well in individual containers for later.
Makes a lot.

title: frozen custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Scald milk.
Pour over eggs.
Put on fire and cook until boiling.
Cool.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla just before freezing.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients until moistened.
Then continue by hand for another minute.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and bake 55 to 65 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: baked alaska
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Add a pinch of salt to egg whites. Beat until stiff, adding sugar gradually until meringue forms stiff peaks.
Add vanilla and a bit of baking powder.
Place cake on a flat pan or cookie sheet, leaving corrugated paper on the bottom for insulation.
Cut a thin slice from the top of the cake using a sharp saw-edge knife or an electric knife and lay the cake slice aside.
Cut out the inside of the cake so that the ice cream, cut in half lengthwise, will fit snugly inside the cake. Replace cake slice and press down firmly.
Spread meringue evenly over the top, sides and both ends of cake until it is completely covered just as you would ice a cake.

title: beth's hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on quartered English muffins. Broil until golden brown (a few minutes).

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pans for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Dice bacon and fry crisp.
Mix with all other ingredients and cook in pressure cooker 1 hour or double boiler 3 hours.

title: holiday dressing
directions: Mix boiled eggs and celery.
Heat chicken broth and chicken and rice soup.
Put 1 stick of butter in broth and soup.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to soup.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except saltines and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and reserved cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Rinse blueberries with water and drain water off.
Mix in a bowl the flour, milk, baking powder, salt, butter and egg.
Mix in blueberries. Scoop out butter.
Pour into heated greased frying pan. Flip when blueberries on top have popped.
Serve hot with butter, syrup or cinnamon sugar.
Enjoy!

title: ants on a log
directions: Fill celery sticks with cream cheese.
Place raisins across the cream cheese.
Voila!
Ants on a log.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over margarine.
Spread condensed milk over crumbs. Sprinkle remaining ingredients in order given. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Mix cheese and spices.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in cheese mixture.
Place on foil-lined cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Make a lip with the foil so the grease won't spill over.

title: peachy-praline pie
directions: Arrange half of peaches in crust.
Mix remaining ingredients, except reserved juice and rest of peaches.
Crumble 1/2 of mixture over peaches in crust.
Repeat with remaining peaches and crumb topping and reserved juice.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°; then reduce heat to 325° until golden brown and set (about 30 more minutes).

title: black forest cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour two 9-inch round layer pans.
Beat flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, salt, baking powder, water, shortening, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.
Prepare cherry filling.
With a vegetable parer, make chocolate curls using the candy bar.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Beat whipping cream and 1/4 cup sugar in chilled bowl until peaks form. Spread bottom layer with 2/3 of cherry filling and 1 cup of the whipped cream.
Top with the second layer.
Spread with remaining cherry filling.
Frost top and sides with remaining whipped cream. If desired, coarsely shred sweet chocolate and press onto side of the cake.
Garnish with chocolate curls and maraschino cherries.

title: mom's devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add 2 beaten egg yolks, plus water. Mix well.
Mix sour milk and soda.
Add to mixture.
Then add flour, salt, cocoa and vanilla.
Beat the two egg whites that were set aside and fold into cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Ice with Brown Sugar Icing.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a frying pan, wok or electric skillet.
When oil is very hot, stir-fry the onions and mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Remove to a bowl.
Add 6 tablespoons more oil to the pan.
Stir-fry the chicken until no longer pink, about 5 minutes.
Return the mushrooms and onions to the skillet.
Add soy sauce and salt for taste.
Remove to a plate and serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: cherry salad jello
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in one cup of boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in remaining boiling water.
Beat together the whipping cream, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon gelatin.
Mix with pineapple and marshmallows.
Spread over cherries and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill until set.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with hot water.
In saucepan, heat cream cheese and milk until cream cheese is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into oblong dish and chill.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Beat cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and frost cake.

title: cheese scrambled eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; beat until well blended. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in moderately hot skillet; pour in egg mixture.
Reduce heat to low.
When mixture starts to set on bottom and sides, lift cooked portions with spatula and turn gently until eggs are cooked but still moist and glossy.
Serves 4.

title: hungarian beef
directions: Season ground beef and fry with onion and bell pepper.
Drain. Add mushroom soup and sour cream. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles on a platter.

title: apple cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Mix shortening and sweetener until blended.
Add egg.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into shortening mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: pineapple crunch pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pastry shell and top with pastry.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini
directions: Cube zucchini; add juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Put in pint jars.
Process 30 minutes in water bath.

title: finska kakor
directions: Mix, chill and roll to 1/4 inch.
Cut in strips.
Brush with 1 egg white, slightly beaten.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/3 cup chopped almonds.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese krispie wafers
directions: Cream cheese and butter; add flour that has been sifted 3 times
with
red
pepper.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Make into small balls
the size of a nickel.
Flatten with finger.
Bake on ungreased
cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.
These will keep well in a tin for a week, also they freeze well.
(Reheat in low temperature oven
to
be
sure
they
are
crisp before serving.)

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions, except omit milk.
Heat processed cheese according to label directions.
Stir ingredients until well blended.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly, but well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg-zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: three potato soup(i usually double.)
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, celery, water and salt in saucepan. Cover and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain.
Mash vegetables slightly.
Stir in milk, butter, parsley and if desired, pepper.
Heat and garnish with green onions.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
If doubled, makes 7 cups.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and pour over the vegetables.
Marinate in fridge 24 hours.
Toss occasionally.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Crush the Ritz crackers and put into mixing bowl.
Add scallops, butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix together until all is moist.
Place shrimp in baking pan and cover with the mixture.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes, until scallops are tender.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring broth and water to a boil.
Scramble egg; pour egg into chicken broth.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into soup bowl and garnish with scallions.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter with fork.
Reserve 2 tablespoons crumbs for garnish.
Press firmly into 9-inch deep pie plate.
Chill 1 hour.
Soften the ice cream; fold in the peanut butter, then fold in whipped cream.
Quickly spoon mixture into crust.
Garnish around edge with remaining crumbs.
Freeze for 5 hours.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slice boiled and skinned potatoes.
Dice 10 hard-boiled eggs, bunch of celery and green onions including 3 Tbsp. of tops (chives).
Fry bacon crisp and crumble into potato mixture. Drizzle 3 Tbsp. bacon grease over mixture.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients together until smooth. Mix together the remaining ingredients.

title: angel food cake with strawberries
directions: Put 1 cup of hot water into the jello and dissolve.
Mix frozen strawberries with jello and allow to thaw.

title: butterscotch filling for cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each new addition.
Gradually add flour.
Blend well with mixer.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix with 1 cup milk and vanilla at high speed for 6 minutes.
Add remaining milk and pie filling mix and blend on low until mixed together.
Then blend on high for 2 minutes.
Pour in pie shell and chill for 4 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and pour over salad mix. Toss salad well and pour bacon on the top.
Keeps well.
(I peel broccoli stalks and slice thin in salad.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix well.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: berry fruit delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add lemon and orange juice. Let cool to set (partially).
Add cottage cheese and yogurt, then add rest of ingredients.
Let set until firm in an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Makes 15 servings.

title: wisconsin potato cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Saute celery and onion until tender.
Add potatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 12 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumber, onion and bell pepper with cup of salt.
Let stand 3 hours in ice water (about 2 trays of ice).
Combine seasoning and vinegar and let boil, then add cucumber, onion and peppers.
Let simmer, but don't let boil because cucumbers get soft.
Pack while hot in jar and seal immediately.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with chili and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Heat in microwave oven for 2 to 3 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve with dip-size Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Suggested recipe to be prepared by a little girl or very tired mother.

title: brisket
directions: Put brisket in large pan and cover brisket with mustard, onion and garlic.
Let stand overnight.
Bake the next day at 200°
for about 2 hours.
Take out.
Put barbecue sauce on and continue baking until done.

title: dipped peanut butter sandwich cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on half of the crackers, a nice thick layer.
Top crackers with peanut butter with remaining crackers to make sandwiches.
Refrigerate.

title: sauteed mushrooms(hongos en mantequilla)
directions: Remove crusts from toast and cut each slice into 4 triangles. Cook and stir onion in margarine and oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except toast and parsley.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Stir in parsley.
Serve over toast triangles. Makes 4 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine vegetables and cover with ice water.
Let stand 3 hours or overnight.
Drain well.
Combine sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seeds and mustard seeds.
Combine everything in a large sauce pan.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Fill jars to within half inch from the top.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In large mixer bowl, stir together sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed of mixer for 2 minutes. Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin). Pour into greased pan. Bake 35 minutes for 2 (9-inch) round pans or 35 to 40 minutes for a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. May frost with Buttercream Icing.

title: apricot salad
directions: Put crushed pineapple, sugar and cream cheese in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes or until cheese is dissolved.
Add box of apricot jello; stir until jello is dissolved.
Add cold water.
Put in a bowl and refrigerate until partially thick.
Then add Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla, then add sifted dry ingredients (cake flour, baking powder, soda and salt), then add bananas and nuts last into mixing bowl.
Pour ingredients into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Coat 2-quart baking dish with margarine or spray with Pam. Cover bottom of dish with undrained pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over pineapple, cover this with dry cake mix.
Slice margarine into small pieces and place on top of cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend shortening and vanilla together.
Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add bananas and dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts, mixing well. Bake in prepared loaf pan at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook together, simmer 1/2 hour or so.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients according to directions on package of cake mix, except chocolate chips. Fold the chips in last with a spoon or spatula.
Put batter in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Make Basic Sweet Dough.
Roll 1/2 batch of dough at once for cinnamon rolls.
Spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll.
Bake at 325° in convection oven 20 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shells and keep in the refrigerator.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove bone and skin.
Cut up and place in baking dish.
Mix broth and celery soup completely.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, then set aside.	Mix flour, salt, pepper, baking powder, margarine and milk.	Pour broth over chicken.
Pour flour mixture over it all.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Layer chicken, broccoli, cheese, onion, bread and soup. Combine eggs, milk and margarine.
Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: very wonderful salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix in strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Pour half into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let Jell-O set. Set aside other half.
Mix a Jell-O cheesecake by box directions. Pour over jellied salad, then spread other half of Jell-O mixture over top.
Let gel again.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread a 9 ounce bowl of Cool Whip over top.
Make sauce and pour over top.

title: cranberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients. Set aside.
In a separate bowl, beat together orange zest, orange juice, oil and water.

Stir into dry ingredients. Add cranberries and mix well. Pour batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan sprayed with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Remove bread from pan and place on wire rack to cool.
Bread slices better the second day.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in iron skillet for 40 minutes.
Will come out better if allowed to cool.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Roll canned biscuits (one at a time) very thin.
Put apple on biscuit.
Fold over crust with fork.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: twinkie cake-dessert
directions: Mix vanilla instant pudding according to directions.
Slice Twinkies in half and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with sliced bananas, then top with instant pudding.
Top pudding with crushed (drained) pineapple.
Last, top with a layer of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix and form into burgers.
Grill or fry until juice runs clear.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Put sugar, water, cinnamon and salt in saucepan (with buttered side).
Cook, stirring until sugar dissolves and it starts to boil.
Cook without stirring to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat about 1 minute until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts (which should still be warm) and stir quickly until nuts are coated. Turn out on waxed paper and separate quickly with two forks.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat butter and add sugars.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats and mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: plum pudding
directions: Cream
butter
and
powdered
sugar.
Add the cider and well beaten
egg
yolks.
When
well mixed, stir in the milk. Cook in a double boiler until it is thick as custard.
Gradually pour it into the beaten egg whites, beating constantly.

title: aunt marjorie's chewy pecan squares
directions: Grease
an
8-inch
square pan.
Stir together the egg, brown sugar
and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Add
pecans.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 18 to
20 minutes
(cookies
should be soft in center when taken from oven). Leave in pan;
cut into 2-inch squares.

title: smachnyky(ukrainian)
directions: Blend softened butter with sugar and beat.
Add yolks; beat some more.
Add crumbled yeast; mix well.
Add flour and put together lightly until all the flour is used up.
Set in refrigerator for 20 minutes.
Form into any desired shape, round balls, crescents, logs, etc.
Brush with beaten egg white; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: peach preserves(from the files of louella scott williams)
directions: Peel and cut up 5 pounds peaches, saving about a dozen peach seeds.
(The original recipe called for washing peaches thoroughly and cutting them up without peeling them, but I like to get rid of the peeling.)
Place in large cooking container with 7 cups of sugar and a half cup of cider vinegar.
Heat to low boil and cook for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
When clear, put in clean jars with one or two seeds per jar.
Seal with melted wax and a good lid.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Thaw frozen hash brown potatoes for 30 minutes.
Combine with all other ingredients except the crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Spread evenly in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over dish top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender and mix until smooth.
May be used in any recipe.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator. (Equals 1 can.)

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Reserve in separate bowl.
Cream butter, then gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs and mashed bananas.
Blend thoroughly.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice and cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat and pour over potatoes.
Top with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add the egg, mixing well.
Then the oil, mixing well.
Add the oats, crushed cornflakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Stir together flour, soda and salt, then add to the oat mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Mix well and form into balls walnut size.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake cookies 12 minutes.
Sprinkle warm cookies with granulated sugar.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: bean burgers
directions: Fry grease out of beef.
Drain off.
Combine beef with soup, onion, diced, catsup and chili powder.
Spread evenly on bun halves.
Broil about four-inches from heat, about 12 or 15 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum pies
directions: Pour 1/4 cup pecans in each frozen pie crust and bake as package directions say.
While pie crust is baking, mix first 3 ingredients (sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese) until smooth. Pour mixture into cooled pie crust.
Top with pie filling and refrigerate.

title: ma rob's broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and onion.
Mix rice and cheese and add broccoli and onion, soup and margarine.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: thumbprints
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Beat until light.
Add flour and vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Dip the balls into egg whites and roll in ground nuts.
Press with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, then push center down again and bake 15 minutes longer.
Remove and put on wire rack.
Fill center with jam or icing.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Blend margarine and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla (mix by hand).
Dough is very stiff.
Pinch off a small piece of dough and roll into finger-like sticks.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Roll Nutty Fingers in powdered sugar while they are still warm.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar again.

title: apple dip
directions: Whip until smooth.
Let stand overnight or at least 2 hours. Use with sliced apples.
You can add a little cinnamon for a yummy taste.

title: avocado and snow crab salad
directions: Dressing:
Drain liquid from snow crab into small bowl.
Add oil, lemon juice and seasonings.
Blend well.

title: lentil soup(low calorie)
directions: In a large stockpot, melt margarine.
Add onion and garlic and saute until soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Place mixture in a blender or the work bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade. Process until well blended.
Serve hot.
Serves 8, 1 cup per serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken,
soups, milk, onion, and noodles and place in baking dish. Top with stuffing mix and cheese. Bake at 350 degree for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: skillet steak and vegetable dinner
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Cut meat into 6 servings.
In a bag, combine salt, flour and pepper.
Shake meat in flour mix. Brown meat in hot oil; transfer meat to platter, leaving oil in skillet.
Brown remainder of flour in skillet.
Stir in tomatoes, dried dill seed and carrots.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add zucchini. Continue cooking for 30 minutes and serve.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Grill over medium hot grill.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Place in casserole in refrigerator overnight.
Crush chips or buttered bread crumbs on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in an 11 x 13-inch pan.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain. Add spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for several minutes. Combine egg, milk and oil in bowl. Add baking mix and salt; mix well.
Spoon ground beef mixture into greased
9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Spoon batter over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown. Cut into squares.

title: sweet chicken curry with yogurt(bangladesh)
directions: In heavy pan, fry 2 tablespoons oil, onions and garlic until soft and lightly brown.
Add ginger, cloves, cardamon, cinnamon, coriander, cumin and red pepper.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, skinned and cut into pieces.
Brown on all sides.
Mix and add yogurt, coconut, raisins and water.
Cover with tight-fitting lid and simmer 35 to 45 minutes until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Mix sugar and Karo together.
Let boil until sugar melts.
Do not overboil.
Then add peanut butter, and stir until getting a little hard.
Add cereal.
Drop with teaspoons on wax paper. After cooled, put Kisses on top.
Makes 60 pieces.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for a few seconds until well mixed. Pour mixture into a deep 10-inch greased pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour or until center tests firm.

title: good ole' vicksburg punch
directions: Boil sugar with water for a few minutes; set aside to cool. Mix oranges, lemons and bananas.
Immediately pour orange and lemon juices over bananas to keep them from darkening.
Add pineapple juice, then add cooled sugar water.
Mix together well. Makes 1 gallon mixture.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix pineapple juice and lemon pudding.
Add chilled fruit.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: buckeyes(cookies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll small amounts of mixture into balls and place on waxed paper on a cookie sheet. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Mix next 4 ingredients with mixer and pour over top of first mixture in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until brown. Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar on top.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Soak chicken wings in salted water for 1 hour.
Put on paper towel and dry.
Put in roasting pan.
Mix soy sauce, sugar and garlic powder.
Marinate overnight.
Turn.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Turn often.
Serve warm.

title: bran buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix bran, boiling water, oleo, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Add part of the flour gradually (about half).
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour; mix and turn out on well floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Shape into buns.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Good to freeze and reheat.

title: new york egg cream
directions: Place chocolate syrup into tall glass. Add milk and stir. Add seltzer and stir.

title: date bars
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool.
In large bowl, sift flour, soda and remaining salt.
Add butter, brown sugar and water, stirring vigorously.
Add oats by hand.

title: mushroom stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place bread cubes in large bowl; set aside. In medium skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, onions, celery, parsley and garlic; cook and stir 2 minutes. Stir in broth, pepper, sage and salt. Pour mixture over bread; toss lightly to mix. Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until heated thoroughly and lightly brown.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Add peanut butter and stir, then add to Rice Krispies.
Spread out on cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Spread over Rice Krispies.
Refrigerate until chocolate solidifies (no longer).

title: braised beef with mushrooms
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Drain mushrooms, saving liquid. Chop garlic and brown with onion and mushrooms in shortening. Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup hot water.
Add with mushroom liquid and remaining ingredients to meat.

title: swiss steak
directions: Slice onions.
Melt margarine in large frying pan on medium heat.
Sprinkle cube steaks with seasoning.
Brown steaks.
Cover with onion slices.
Pour whole tomatoes with juice over steak and onions.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook about 10 minutes.

title: best ever biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, add shortening and blend together. Pour milk into flour mixture slowly.
Add the egg.
Stir to a soft dough.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: davey crocket bars
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Press into jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the eggs until light and foamy. Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly, but well. Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg-zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Measure before using, put a small amount in blender and blend until powder.

title: pineapple sherbet punch
directions: Put lemonade, orange juice and carbonated water in punch bowl and stir.
Fold in sherbet and ice cream.
Serve at once.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: creamy cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth, gradually beat in sugar, blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Put in pie crust. Top with sliced fresh strawberries or sliced kiwi.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat egg, buttermilk, brown sugar and oil together.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened, slightly lumpy.
Makes 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Melt in skillet or pan the oleo.
Add onion and garlic and cook until soft.
Add ground beef and brown well.
Stir in and simmer for 15 minutes for rich sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms, water, celery, green pepper, cheese, salt and pepper to taste. Cook noodles until tender.
Drain noodles and mix with sauce and ground beef.
Heat for 1 hour and serve.

title: frozen banana punch
directions: At least 2 days in advance, mix and boil sugar and water for 3 minutes. Set aside and cool. In a large bowl, squeeze 1-1/2 lemons. Add the orange juice and the mashed bananas. Add the pineapple juice, and then the sugar and water. Freeze in a large bowl.

title: hash brown-ham casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sour cream and chicken soup.
Stir in potatoes, ham, Velveeta and onion.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch dish. Combine cornflakes and melted butter, sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix these ingredients together until pudding is dissolved. Add sliced bananas as desired.

title: syrup
directions: Mix all
together
and bring to boil and let cook until thickens.
Ready for use and keep in refrigerator.

title: pork chops in sour cream
directions: Rub pork chops with a mixture of sage, salt and a dash of pepper.
Brown lightly on both sides in hot shortening.
Drain off excess fat. Add onions.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is done.
Place meat on serving platter.

title: orange pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, combine cookie mix, butter, egg, orange extract and pecans. Mix well. Drop by heaping spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned around edges. Remove from oven and let cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute. Transfer cookies to cooling rack. Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add milk and oleo.
Cook 2 minutes after it boils.
Remove from heat at once.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and drop from spoon on waxed paper or a buttered platter.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and then add alternately with the buttermilk.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and butter flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes beautifully.

title: fruit slushes
directions: Mix all ingredients and fill plastic cups 2/3 full. Freeze. May thaw before serving. Number of servings: 12.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix soup, vinegar, mustard, sugar, oil and salt and pepper. Put on stove and heat, then pour over carrots.
Serve cold.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine next 7 ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Beat Dream Whip with milk; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine maraschino cherries, pineapple chunks and marshmallows. Beat cream cheese with salad dressing.
Add to the pineapple mixture.
Fold in the Dream Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Freeze overnight.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: superb stroganoff
directions: Add 2 teaspoons vegetable oil and steak strips to skillet; brown.
Set aside.
In same skillet, add onions and mushrooms and saute until mushrooms are tender.
Add meat, sour cream, parsley and seasonings.
Stir over low heat until thoroughly heated. Place noodles on serving platter.
Top with meat and sauce mixture.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup boiling water; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat 4 eggs well, add vegetable oil and mix.
Stir in 1 box cake mix (dry) and lemon extract; beat well.
Add jello mixture, stirring well.
Pour into a tube pan lined on bottom with wax paper.
Bake 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain whole kernel corn.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Delicious.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans; mix well.
Pour into pretty mold or bowl. Store in refrigerator until ready.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then cut in butter and stir in raisins.
Blend egg, milk and pumpkin or squash.
Add to dry mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Do not overmix.
Bake in greased muffin tin at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(May sprinkle sugar or cinnamon on top.)

title: johnny muzzetti
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles and add.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey cake
directions: Put one cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in bowl with lid. Cut 2 packs of biscuits into 1/4 and put into sugar mixture. Shake.
In pot, melt margarine, rest of sugar and cinnamon until syrupy.
Pour 1/2 over biscuits.
Do remaining 2 packs of biscuits as the first batch.
Pour rest of syrup over this.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken sauce
directions: Combine and pour over raw chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Test for doneness.
May need longer baking depending on size of fryer.

title: tiramisu
directions: Pour 1/2 cup milk into blender; add cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Add 1 cup of milk.
Dissolve coffee in hot water and add to blender with Kahlua.
Blend until smooth.
Next, gently stir in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers, split in half.
Cover ladyfingers with half of mixture.
Make a second layer of ladyfingers and top with remaining mixture.
Top with ladyfingers and grated chocolate for decorating.
Chill until firm (several hours or overnight).

title: peanut butter swirl
directions: Cream the peanut butter, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Top with a cup of chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Take out and marble with knife. Bake 25 to 30 minutes more until done.

title: southern hushpuppies
directions: Mix all together, form into 1 1/2-inch balls and deep fry until golden brown. Serve hot.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and thinly slice apples into a 6 x 10-inch Pammed baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spoon cranberry sauce over apples.
In bowl, combine oats, flour and brown sugar; cut in margarine.
Sprinkle over cranberry layers. Bake until apples are cooked through about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pink tropical fluff
directions: Whip first 4 ingredients together with a mixer.
Add pecans and mix well.
Serve in party glasses and garnish with strawberries or pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Store in refrigerator.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk in a large saucepan.
Cook and stir on medium heat until thickened. Beat eggs lightly with wire whisk.
Add a little hot mixture to eggs and blend well.
Pour eggs into mixture in saucepan.
Continue cooking for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend mixture well.
Cover pudding.
Cool slightly. Place layer of vanilla wafers on bottom of casserole dish. Alternate with layers of banana slices and pudding, ending with pudding on top.
Put dish in the center of preheated oven of 350°. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix all dry ingredients. Coat chicken with mixture.
Brown chicken in some of the bacon fat (about 1/2 cup).

Arrange chicken in casserole dish. Add onion, pepper and mushrooms to fat in skillet; saute for 5 minutes. Add soup and bacon; bring to a boil. Pour over chicken. May top with slivered almonds. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: easy broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth, salt and water.
Add onion, peppers, broccoli and cheese.
Bake in a dish or pan at 375° about 1/2 hour, until it bubbles.

title: madeline's milk shake
directions: Blenderize all of the ingredients together with some cubes. Makes 2.

title: bean burritos
directions: Combine first two ingredients, set aside.
Spoon heaping 1/2 cup bean mixture and 1 tablespoon cheese onto center of each tortilla.
Roll up tortilla to enclose filling.
Place seam side down in 11 x 7-inch microwavable dish.
Pour taco sauce evenly over burritos.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Loosely cover dish. Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until heated through.
If desired, garnish with lettuce, tomato and black olives.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and green pepper into sterilized jars. Make juice of rest of ingredients; heat until melts.
Cool; pour over cukes.
Store in refrigerator for weeks.
Wait a week before using.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix together margarine and sugar; add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Sift and add dry ingredients.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In sauce pan combine chocolate chips, milk and butter. Cook stirring constantly over medium heat, until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows and peanuts. Spread in 8 x 8 x 2 greased pan.

title: slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and sugar.
Cool.
Boil at the same time the tea bags in 2 cups water.
Let this cool.
After cool, add orange juice and lemonade.
Combine all and add booze.
Makes about 1/2 ice cream bucket.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix meat with soup mix, breadcrumbs and egg; make meatballs. Combine ketchup, apple jelly, butter and Tabasco.
Stir until jelly melts and make sure ingredients are mixed thoroughly.
Drop meatballs in crock-pot and cook on high for 1 hour, then reduce heat to low for 1 hour.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine nuts, cookie crumbs, 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, cocoa, corn syrup and liquor of choice.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls. Combine 1/2 cup powdered sugar with coffee and roll cookies in mixture.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine butter, peanut butter, vanilla and powdered sugar. Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip balls into the chocolate. Place balls on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Put into freezer for 2 minutes.
Remove from freezer and store in a cool place.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix cooking oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large bowl.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nuts or raisins.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mary's peanut patties
directions: Mix all ingredients; bring to a slow boil.
Cook until it spins a thread (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Remove from heat, then add 1 stick of margarine and a few drops of red food coloring. Let cool and beat until creamy.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: n.j. blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix blueberries, sugar and cinnamon.
Cover bottom of an 8-inch square lightly greased pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Blend sugar, egg, milk, shortening and vanilla. Pour blended mixture over flour mixture and stir until smooth. Cover blueberry mixture with batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve warm with milk.

title: cabbage-tomato casserole
directions: Brown chicken or turkey and onions.
Put in the rest of ingredients.
Best to simmer for a good two hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add tomatoes and chicken. Stir into spaghetti.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Wheat Thins and butter, and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Combine crushed Wheat Thins with melted butter.
Place on top of casserole and cook for 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: greek salad with broiled shrimp(low-carb)
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Remove veins.
Place shrimp in a small bowl and toss with 2 Tbsp. olive oil, garlic, 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper.
Thread the shrimp onto a metal skewer and place on a baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining shrimp.
Broil about 2 to 3 minutes, until tops are browned and then flip to brown other side.
Set shrimp aside.

title: quick creamy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips over medium heat.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and eat.

title: percolator punch 2
directions: Mix cranberry cocktail juice, pineapple juice and brown sugar together.
Pour in 32-cup percolator.
Now place whole cloves, sticks of cinnamon and sliced orange in percolator basket.
Plug in and perk. Serve from percolator.
A good Christmas punch. Serves 25.

title: grilled chicken and sausage skewers with herb vinaigrette
directions: Place sausages in a large saucepan.
Add enough cold water to cover.
Cook until firm and cooked through.
Slice each in thirds. Mix oil, lemon juice, vinegar, garlic, mustard, herbes de provence, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Place chicken and sausages in a shallow dish.
Pour half of vinaigrette over and reserve the other half for basting.
Add lemon slices and bay leaves.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Skewer chicken, sausages, onions and peppers, as desired.
Grill and baste with remaining marinade, about 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 sticks melted butter and crumbs.
Pat into oblong pan.
Beat together 2 sticks soft butter, eggs and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread this over crumbs.
Slice bananas over this.
Drain pineapple and pour over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip and top with nuts and cherries.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars and cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Pinch off dough and roll into 1-inch balls. Place on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Press with tines of a fork to flatten.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until golden. Cool on wire rack.
Yields 5 to 7 dozen.

title: low fat french fries
directions: Slice potatoes in french fry style. Toss with dressing and place on sprayed baking sheet. Spray top of potatoes with cooking spray like Pam. Salt to taste and bake at 400° for approximately 25 minutes. Turn once during cooking time. Serves 6. Per serving: 2 g. fat, 0 g. sugar, 5 g. fiber, 100 calories.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender. Drain in colander and turn into 2-quart casserole. Add soup, milk, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and tuna.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir all ingredients together. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, one at a time. Roll into balls. Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until brown.
Will make 25 to 30 balls.

title: chicken pie
directions: In a large baking dish, melt butter.
Layer chicken and sliced boiled eggs.
Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth together.
Pour over chicken.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Divide in half for 1 punch bowl.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Soften cream cheese. Beat with mixer.
Add next three ingredients and beat until fluffy. Put a vanilla wafer in bottom of each cupcake liner. Fill halfway with filling.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool to room temperature. Top with cherry, blueberry or any other pie filling.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan with waxed paper lined bottom.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on waxed paper.
Cool.
Cut into bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Line pan with bread.
Add meat and cheese (in layers).
Mix eggs, milk and remaining ingredients in separate bowl; pour over mixture.
Cover with more cheese (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. (Can be prepared the night before.)

title: finger paint recipe
directions: Cook and stir until smooth.
Tint with coloring to make small amounts of different colors.
Baby food jars are ideal to store paint in.

title: lambs butter cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk.
Gradually add flour.
Make into balls and press down with two fingers.
Do not grease pans.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: fumi(coleslaw)
directions: Brown sesame seeds and almonds in butter.
Mix cabbage and onions in a large bowl.
Crush Ramen noodles; toss with flavor packet.
Just before serving, combine sesame seeds, almonds and crushed noodles with the cabbage and onion.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chunked chicken into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat soup in small saucepan with 1 can full of milk and 1/2 can full of water until mixed well and warm.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on box, then cover chicken and soup with stuffing.
Top with 4 to 5 butter pats.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower according to directions on package.
Place in mixing bowl and stir 30 seconds.
Scrape bowl and stir.
Beat on No. 4 speed.
Change to whip for 30 seconds.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix again for 30 seconds.
Place in 3-cup casserole dish.
Mix remaining butter and stuffing on top and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put orange and cranberries through food chopper.
Add sugar. Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cold water and orange juice. Chill until thickened.
Fold into cranberry, orange mixture. Add celery and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: nancy's beans
directions: In saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Add beans, cheese and soup.
Put in casserole dish and top with Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350 degree oven until hot.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut flour, lard or Crisco, baking powder, salt and sugar together until coarsely crumbled.
Add beaten egg with vinegar and water.
Refrigerate 20 minutes to use or divide in about 6 portions and put between wax paper.
Put in Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix all together until smooth. Pour in a well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces with friends helping (may take 2 months).
Cover with brown gravy.
Cook over kerosene fire for 4 weeks at 465°.
Will serve 3,850 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and part of milk.
Beat.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder. Add, alternating with remainder of milk and mashed bananas.
Beat well.
Bake at 365° about 35 minutes.

title: after church stew
directions: Place beef (no need to brown it) in 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrots and onions.
Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables, coating all pieces.
Cover tightly.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Make a smooth paste.
Add hot milk.
Cook broccoli until tender in the chicken bouillon.
Add to the flour mixture.
Heat for serving and add the cheese; allow the cheese to melt before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, egg, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger together. Add hot water. Beat everything together, then pour into pie shell. Cook for 50 to 55 minutes in oven set at 375°.
Cool and eat.

title: whip cream frosting
directions: Beat ingredients until creamy for about 8 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and stir all ingredients. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 10 minutes. Stir well.
Bake another 10 minutes. Add 1 cup grated sharp Cheddar cheese on top. Bake 15 more minutes or until light brown.

title: beef and beer casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients and place in covered casserole.
Cook at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: boiled custard
directions: Combine milk, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into milk mixture.
Simmer over hot water (double boiler).
Will take 5 hours or more.
It will thicken as it simmers.
When thick enough, sprinkle with nutmeg and chill.

title: layered wild rice and asparagus
directions: Cook wild rice according to package directions.
Combine soup (or sauce whichever you use), onion and sour cream.
Place wild rice on the bottom of a casserole.
Lay asparagus spears on top. Pour sauce over asparagus, then top with cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk, salt and baking powder together.
Melt butter in pan, put sweetened fruit in and pour flour mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.,

title: wild rice apple bake
directions: Place contents of rice and seasoning packets in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter.
Add apples and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cook until apples are lightly glazed.
Add celery, raisins and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over rice, stir and cover. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover, stir and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fluffy icing
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Cook until thick.
Cover and set aside to cool.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar together. Whip everything together.
Put onto cooled cake.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Then add wet ingredients. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 450° or until brown. Pour 1 cup melted butter over top.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Put eggs, sugar, vinegar and 1 tablespoon butter in saucepan; cook over very low heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon. After mixture begins to heat, add remaining butter and cook, still stirring, until thickens.
Use on potato salad, cole slaw or garden salad.

title: gramma brown's doctored baked beans
directions: Cook onion partially in microwave oven.
Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Put in casserole dish; place bacon on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° to 400° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly and bacon is crisp.

title: baked tomatoes florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small pan, cook mushrooms and onion in water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine milk, flour and bouillon over low heat.
Cook and stir until it thickens.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Combine mushroom mixture, chicken, spinach and 3/4 cup sauce mix.
Stuff into tomatoes.
Cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes until hot.
Heat remaining sauce with 1 to 2 tablespoons of water.
Spoon over tomatoes.

title: crab delights cream cheese cocktail spread
directions: Place cream cheese on serving plate.
Top with cocktail sauce and crab delights.
Garnish with fresh thyme or parsley, if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Add 1 cup sugar and 1 cup hot water until dissolved, then add rhubarb; set aside.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain and mix all vegetables.
Mix sugar, cider vinegar, salad oil and water until dissolved and pour over vegetables.
Store vegetables in covered container.
They may be served after being stored overnight in refrigerator.

title: mussels (or clams) mariniere
directions: In a bowl, pour Cajun seasoning over shrimp and toss to coat. Discard any excess spice mixture.
Heat a large skillet and melt butter until it sizzles.
Saute walnuts and celery in melted butter over a medium to high heat for approximately two minutes, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and cook, turning regularly until shrimp are well curled and opaque (approximately five minutes). Add honey and green onions and blend well.
Turn heat to medium and cook two more minutes.
Serve immediately over rice.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Soak lima beans according to package directions. Drain, reserving liquid. Add enough water to measure 12 cups liquid.
In a large saucepan, combine beef flavor granules, barley, lima beans and liquid. Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: pineapple bean soup
directions: Cook for 1 hour and after it cools you can play Hawaiian music.

title: shirley's rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix rice, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla. Bake until thick; remove.
Prepare pudding and cook until slightly thick.
Pour over rice mixture.
Place in oven for more cooking.
Remove when starting to brown.
Beat egg whites; prepare for pie topping.
Add to rice pudding and brown or use whipped topping (either is wonderful).
Serve warm or cold.
This makes a wonderful dish for someone who can't eat sugar.
This recipe is low in fat and sugar.

title: english muffin bread(fat free bread)
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and yeast; combine water, sugar and salt and add to flour and yeast.
Beat at low speed on electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl; then beat at high for 3 minutes (optional:
add wheat germ and water at this time).
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Shape into ball; place in lightly greased bowl, turning to grease dough's surface. Cover; let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Punch down; let rise 10 minutes and shape into rolls, small loaves or a single loaf (1-quart casserole).
Grease pan(s) and sprinkle cornmeal over shaped dough.
Cover; let rise until double (30 to 40 minutes). Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes (1 loaf), 15 to 20 minutes (rolls), 20 to 25 minutes (small loaves).
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, eggs
and butter.
Add flour to sugar and blend into egg
mixture.	Stir
in
vanilla and coconut.	Pour into pie shell.
Bake
at
400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until set and browned.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla all at once.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer. Note:
Batter will be very thin.
Pour batter into a greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: picadillo(yield:  4 servings)
directions: 1. Cook rice according to package directions.

title: bird in a nest
directions: Coat both sides of bread slice with margarine.
Cut a disc out of the center of each slice with a glass or cookie cutter, leaving a hole in the bread slice, which will become a nest.
Brown bread (nest and disc) in skillet like a pancake.
When nest is turned over in pan, brown bottom as you drop 1 teaspoon margarine in nest to melt.
Reduce heat to low.
Carefully drop raw egg into nest and cook slowly until ready to either flip for overeasy or remove and serve sunny side up.
Serve with disc topped with syrup or jam of your choice.

title: idiot proof chicken
directions: Stir together everything, except chicken and butter, in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Lay chicken on top.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garlic salt is good on this. Bake, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses and mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into round ball.
Refrigerate. Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, eggs and salt.
Beat slightly and put into a baking dish.
Add corn.
Top with grated cheese.
You may add chopped green pepper or oysters, if desired.
Bake for 45 min. at 350°.

title: mashed potato souffle
directions: In a large bowl combine mashed potatoes, heavy cream, onion and 1 teaspoon salt.
Into the potato mixture, beat in the stick of softened butter, 2 egg yolks and salt and white pepper to taste.
In another bowl beat the 4 egg whites with a pinch of salt and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold this into the potato mixture.
Put the souffle into a buttered 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top it with the onion slices, brush it with butter and bake it for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
This recipe should not be doubled.

title: gooey cheese bars
directions: Mix these and pour over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut into small squares.
Very rich!!!

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine thoroughly in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for one minute, remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and let cool for a few minutes.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper or oiled cookie sheet. Let cool.

title: nancy's linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini and drain. Set in mixing bowl. Add Salad Supreme and toss. Add Viva Italian dressing and toss again.
Cut up all vegetables (small size) and add to the linguini mixture. Cover and let sit in refrigerator overnight and then it is ready to serve. Stir before serving.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken until cooked. Break into small pieces. Heat soup. Mix celery, mayonnaise, onion, slivered almonds, pimento and add to soup. Pour into greased casserole dish along with chicken. Cover with 1/2-inch of Pepperidge Farm mix. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put the first six ingredients together in large crock or glass or stainless bowl and let stand overnight.
Drain and add the vinegar, mustard seed, sugar, turmeric and celery seed.
Bring to a boil, pack into jars and seal.
Makes 14 quarts.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Mix soda with sour cream and add.
Sift salt, cocoa and flour; add to mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13 pan and bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil three cups of water and add the 2 cups of Minute Rice and cook until done.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli until done.
In a large pot, mix together broccoli, rice, soup and cheese; pour into a large baking dish.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.
Let stand for 1 hour before serving.

title: masie's mom's southern sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix topping ingredients well and spoon over other mixture. Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Eat and enjoy.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook the eggplant until tender and drain.
Add the salt and pepper.
Mash. Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Add to the eggplant. Grease casserole dish with butter.
Pour mixture into dish. Add enough sweet milk to cover.
Cook at 375° until milk is absorbed, about 1/2 hour. Cover with grated cheese.
Let cheese melt in oven.

title: pepperoni quiche brunch
directions: Start browning pepperoni in a cold skillet over low heat (let the meat juices come out).
Add shortening to the meat juices to cover the skillet bottom evenly.
Turn to medium heat.
Add potatoes (cubed) and allow to brown to taste.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Flour and lightly salt chicken.
Brown in hot fat.
Remove to flat casserole.
Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken - no peek
directions: Sprinkle rice mix in buttered oblong baking dish.
Mix soups and water; pour over rice mix.
Arrange chicken in dish.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover dish tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: famous lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat egg yolk.
Add to cornstarch mixture.
Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling, then boil gently for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Slowly beat in 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread meringue over pie, covering and sealing to the edge.
Bake at 425° for 4 to 5 minutes, until brown.
Cool before serving.

title: animal or alphabet cracker necklaces
directions: Melt candy coating in small saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spread candy coating generously on flat side of 4 animal crackers.
Place one pretzel in the coating on each cracker, leaving top two holes of pretzel open to allow for threading ribbon of necklace.
Allow to set.
Repeat with remaining candy coating, animal crackers and pretzels.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, pumpkin, salt, cloves, ginger and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in milk.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.
If fresh pumpkin is used, use less milk.

title: broccoli topped tuna bake
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package.
Drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz cheese spread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except corn flakes) well.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 375° for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Boil noodles with bouillon cube. Brown garlic, onion and ground beef in butter. Add remaining ingredients. Let it cook 5 minutes. Add one can of diluted cream of chicken soup and simmer for 10 minutes. Keeping heat low, stir in 3/4 cup sour cream. Heat thoroughly on low so cream won't curdle. Stir in noodles and serve.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter; add flour and seasonings; gradually add scalded milk, stirring until smooth.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Add diced chicken and minced parsley.
Cool.
Shape.
Dip in beaten egg; roll in finely sifted bread or cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat (365°) until well browned.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve with cream peas or chili sauce.

title: italian beef
directions: Cover in a casserole and bake at 325° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours or put in crock-pot in the morning and serve at supper.

title: sweet and sour peas
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pineapple.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with pineapple slices.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes in salted water until soft, then rub through strainer.
Scald milk with onions.
Remove onions and add milk, stirring, to potatoes.
Melt half the butter and add flour, salt, celery salt, pepper and cayenne.
Stir until well mixed and then stir into hot soup.
Boil for 1 minute.
Strain and add the remaining butter.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: In small bowl combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard; set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine eggs, onion, bread crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper. Add 1/2 cup of tomato sauce mixture and stir thoroughly. Place meat mixture in a greased glass (Pyrex-type) ring mold or a round 2 quart microwave safe casserole dish with a small pyrex cup, inverted in the middle for the ring. Pour remaining tomato sauce on top of the meat. Cover with a sheet of wax paper and cook on high (max. power) in microwave for 12-14 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Blend all ingredients with wooden spoon until thoroughly blended.
Shape teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thick with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: applesauce oatmeal pancakes
directions: In a bowl, combine the oats, flours and baking powder.
In another bowl, combine milk, applesauce and egg whites; add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter by 1/4 cupful onto a heated griddle coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook until bubbles appear on the top; turn and cook until lightly browned. Yields 5 servings.

title: jello layered salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 3/4 cups boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple, juice and all.
Add frozen strawberries.
Chill mixture until slightly jelled.
Put half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch glass loaf pan.
Slice bananas on top and refrigerate until very firm.

title: vegetable pizza (appetizer)
directions: Press crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake as directed on the package.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayo or yogurt and dressing mix and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Top with chopped veggies, olives and grated cheese.
Use your imagination!
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add butter, milk, sour cream, eggs and oil.
Add whole kernel corn, green chilies, onion and Cheddar cheese and enough oil to cover bottom of skillet or pan.
(I use cast-iron skillet.)
If batter is too thick, add more milk.
Bake at 375° to 400° until brown, as desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in broccoli, rice and onion. Melt together cheese, butter and milk.
Add soup and sour cream. Pour over broccoli mixture.
Stir and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nancyburgers
directions: Add oatmeal to the other ingredients until no longer sticky.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together butter and sugar. Mix in eggs and banana, blending until smooth. In another bowl, stir together all-purpose flour, salt, baking soda and whole-wheat flour until thoroughly blended. Add to banana mixture alternately with hot water. Stir in nuts. Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until bread begins to pull away from sides of pan and a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a rack and let cool completely. Makes 1 loaf.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Combine croutons and cheese.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Pour over crouton mixture.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon or sausage on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Slice fruit
with
peel
left
on;
soak fruit in lemon juice and water
for 30 minutes.	Mix 1/4 cup brown sugar, the cinnamon, nutmeg
and
Cool Whip together.
Arrange drained fruit on serving plate and serve with dip.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together baking soda and boiling water, add sugar, shortening, eggs, bananas, flour, salt and walnuts.
Mix well. Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: baked tomato casserole
directions: Put half of the tomatoes in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the salt, pepper and sugar.
Dot with half the butter. Top with half the cheese and half the bread, broken in pieces. Finish with remaining ingredients in the same order.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rigatoni alla carbonara
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper and cook on grill or grill pan. Let stand until pasta is done. Place a large pot of water on the stove to boil. When water is rolling, add salt and pasta and cook to al dente, about 8 minutes, reserving 1/4 cup of water.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix the flour, cornmeal and coconut with sugar.
Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 uncooked pie crusts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Layer with graham crackers. Graham crackers bottom layer, 1/2 pudding mixture on top, graham crackers next layer then rest of pudding.
Graham crackers on top and then frost with milk chocolate frosting.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Crush wafers.
Add alternately with milk.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Bake in prepared Bundt pan for about 75 minutes at 325°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute steak strips in 1/2 cup butter until brown. Dissolve bouillon in 1 cup water and add to meat. Add paste, mustard and salt. Simmer for 45 minutes, covered. Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic in remainder of butter until onion is tender. Combine flour and 1/2 cup water; reduce heat and add flour mixture to meat. Heat until slightly thickened. Add mushrooms and onion mixture. Stir and heat together. Just before serving, add sour cream. Heat but do not boil. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: clam linguini
directions: Start cooking linguini.
Drain clam juice and set aside.
Saute olive oil and garlic (minced).
Stir in clam juice, parsley, wine and spices.
Heat through and serve over linguini.
Great with garlic bread and Caesar salad.

title: butterscotch coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Put half of the batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with half of crumb mixture (follows).
Add other half of batter and remaining crumbs.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Unroll crescent dough one section at a time.
Cut each section into fifths.
Wrap each section of dough around sausage and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°, about 8 to 10 minutes until dough is golden brown.
Makes 40 to 50 hors d'oeuvres.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and nutmeg until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Stir in bananas and vanilla.
Combine flour, powder, soda and salt.
Beat into mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: holiday spice potpourri
directions: Peel and cut up fresh peaches.
Put into copper boiler.
Add sugar to taste.
A long ladle is used to push the peaches back and forth.
After peach butter has cooked down, it is put into jars for the winter.

title: blender double fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Measure nuts into blender; chop on low speed.
Set nuts aside.
In order listed, measure remaining ingredients except chocolate pieces into blender.

title: jim's pimento cheese
directions: Coarsely grate cheese.
Drain pimento and process fine. Combine all ingredients; stir well and chill.
Serve with crackers, regular or toasted sandwiches.

title: crumb cake
directions: Beat for 5 minutes.
Grease a 17 x 12 x 1 1/2 inches deep pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Clean carrots and slice thin.
Cook and drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine milk, cheese, onion/margarine mixture and soup.
Add carrots.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 3 minutes or until melted. Add graham cracker crumbs and remaining ingredients, layering in the order listed. (Do not stir.) Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool completely in pan. Cut into bars. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: pier 4 cheese dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter, adding cheese in small amounts.
Add horseradish, worcestershire and sherry. Serve at room temperature.

title: sinfully good chicken
directions: Place cubed chicken in greased casserole.
Combine soups and cream cheese; pour over chicken.
Prepare stuffing according to directions and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: simply elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Brown in oil.
Add onions.
Saute until tender crisp.
Add remaining ingredients; reduce heat to simmer for about 1 hour.
Serve over a bed of fluffy rice.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth (do not drain). Combine all other ingredients with cooked pasta except Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with Cheddar cheese; let melt and serve.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in casserole dish.
Mix together sugar, salt, flour, egg and baking powder and then spread over apples.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake for about 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: "any idiot" lemon pie
directions: Mix together the lemonade and milk.
Then fold in Cool Whip. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Refrigerate.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Combine Ritz, melted oleo and sugar. Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Press into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Blend pudding, ice cream and milk.
Pour over crust.
