Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, top with 1 small container of Cool Whip and garnish with reserved crumb mixture.
Can be made with any flavor of pudding and ice cream.

title: cracker fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring while cooking. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all the ingredients and pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend peanut butter, sugar and cream cheese in mixer until creamy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until serving time.
Can be topped with whipped topping.
Can use graham cracker crust.

title: malt shop ice cream ring
directions: Crush milk balls (best in food processor); set aside.
Fold together softened ice cream with Cool Whip, stirring well but not beating.
Stir in milk balls and pour into jello ring.
Pour enough graham cracker crumbs over ice cream to form crust.
Seal and freeze at least 2 hours before serving.

title: rice krispie chicken
directions: Melt butter. Crush Rice Krispies. Dip chicken in butter and then dip in Rice Krispies. Put in glass dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Cover with foil when done.

title: ham glaze
directions: Bring honey, brown sugar and orange juice to a boil.
Pour this mixture and Coke over ham.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Baste ham with glaze during baking.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Measure shortening and flour and blend together with salt. Mix eggs, water and vinegar together, then add to flour mixture. When dough holds together, roll out with rolling pin and use as usual.
Makes 5 crusts and will refrigerate for 2 weeks, or may be frozen and defrosted for later use.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans; wash and drain kidney beans.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: roll dumplings
directions: Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening, then add milk. Roll into a rectangle and cut into strips.
Drop 1-inch pieces into boiling soup or stew.
Cook about 15 minutes.

title: rocky road chocolate drops
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips, butter and milk. Remove from heat and add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and refrigerate for several hours.
If desired, pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for several hours and cut into squares.

title: almond float
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/3 cup cold water.
Add hot water and sugar.
Stir.
Pour in almond extract and milk.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until gelatin sets.
Cut into bite size squares.
Mix with fruit cocktail or choice of fruits. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk; stir well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; boil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.

Add next 3 ingredients and pecans, if desired; stir until chocolate and butter are melted. Quickly spread mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Allow candy to cool for at least 2 hours. Cut fudge into 1-inch squares.
Yield: 30 (1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: cauliflower shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Cut shrimp in half if large.
Chop green pepper and onion.
Separate cauliflower so flowerets are as tiny as possible.
Cut olives in slices.
Mix rest of ingredients. Serve well chilled.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat until fluffy and smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust (chocolate is best).
Freezes well.

title: calico salad
directions: Cook the frozen vegetables.
Drain well.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: stickies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into medium bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Remove one cup of flour mixture to a small bowl.
Blend it with milk to form a paste. Add paste to first mixture and mix just enough to hold dough together.
Place on a lightly floured board and knead lightly. Roll out to oblong shape, about 10 x 18-inches.
Mix cinnamon, sugar and softened margarine.
Spread on dough and roll lengthwise in jelly roll fashion.
Seal edges.
Cut slices 3/4 to 1 inch thick.
Place on a greased pan and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate meat, onion and beans.
Chill.
Toss together with meat mixture the tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Add crushed taco chips and dressing just before serving.

title: crullers
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together until thoroughly mixed.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with cream to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Place dough on floured board and pat and roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into 6 x 1-inch strips.
Twist dough and press ends together.
Fry a few at a time in hot, deep fat (360°) until brown; drain.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: no carb dessert
directions: Crush nuts. Mix with the butter (melted). Spread on bottom of pie plate; refrigerate. Mix all the other ingredients. Spread over nuts and chill.

title: deep-fried quail
directions: Dip each piece of quail in milk and roll in seasoned flour or toss the quail and flour together in paper bag.
Brush each piece lightly with well beaten egg yolk.
Drop the coated quail into piping hot fat, putting in only 2 or 3 pieces at a time so that the fat won't drop to a low temperature.
(This precaution keeps the quail from becoming grease-soaked.)
You can tell when the birds are done by their rich golden-brown color and by the fact that they float slightly in the hot fat.
Remove the cooked pieces from the fat, being careful not to pierce the flesh with a fork; if you do, you'll break the crust and the juices will run out.
Drain on absorbent paper and keep hot until ready to serve, which shouldn't be too long after cooking.
Serve 1 1/2 quails per person.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add melted butter, eggs, buttermilk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until firm, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8. Very rich!

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour; slightly beat eggs and stir into sugar and flour.
Cut oleo into mixture; add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Add potatoes and mix well.
Pour into pastry shells. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: In a medium bowl, lightly beat sugar and eggs.
Add corn syrup, pecans, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 25 minutes or just until edges are lightly browned.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheese and sausage dish
directions: Brown sausage; drain and add vegetables.
Continue cooking 5 minutes and drain.
Set aside to cool 10 minutes.
Stir together sausage mixture, cheese spread and bread cubes.
Place in greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: gram spencer's ginger cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Flour enough to roll into balls, so you can handle
it.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Combine egg and milk; add gradually to flour, mixing only until smooth.
Add shortening.
Baked on hot greased griddle.
Makes 10 pancakes.

title: sausage 'n egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat and drain quickly.
(I use paper towels to press out as much fat as possible.)
Use sausage grease to grease a 2-quart casserole dish (a 13 x 9 x 2-inch is ideal) and distribute browned sausage evenly over surface of dish.
In a separate 2-quart bowl, break eggs; stir in milk, salt and cheese. Both containers may be refrigerated overnight and allowed to reach room temperature in the early morning.
Using medium speed on your mixer, beat egg mixture.
Pour evenly over sausage.
Sprinkle croutons over top, pushing them very lightly into the egg mixture. Bake uncovered in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving in a casserole frame or on cake racks to prevent sogginess underneath.
Yields 6 to 8 generous servings and is not untasty as a leftover.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail, 1 1/3 cups (1 packet) of coconut and eggs in large mixer bowl. Blend; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Bring butter, granulated sugar and milk to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining coconut.
Spoon over warm cake.
Top with prepared whipped topping, if desired.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Cook
carrots,	celery,
onion	and
English peas until tender.
Add pimento, water chestnuts, soup, corn and chicken. Mix together.
Use 8
x
12-inch baking dish, line bottom with crushed corn chips.
Put mixture in baking dish and pour about 1/4 cup chicken broth
around
side
of dish.
Top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cran raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sauce and chill until partially set.
Thaw the raspberries and drain well, then fold into the partially set jello.
Fold in nuts, chill and set until firm.
Enjoy!

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onions.
Fry onions.
Add to potatoes; onion, corn, butter, milk and crushed bacon.
Heat until hot, but do not boil.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: caramelized onions
directions: Peel onions and remove stems and root ends.
Place in slow cooker.
Pour butter and broth over.
Cook on low for 12 hours. Serve as a side dish or over any meat.

title: sunshine slush
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Garnish with an orange slice and a cherry.

title: snow peas with red pepper
directions: Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium high heat until hot.
Add snow peas and sweet red pepper; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add garlic, sesame seed and seasonings.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring mixture constantly.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix well. Marinate chicken, grill or broil.

title: italian dressing
directions: Put in a jar and shake.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and water; beat.
Add flour and spices.
Add pumpkin and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 4 large loaves.

title: lib's lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter, and nuts.
Press into 9 X 13 pan and bake at 350 for 20 minutes (slightly brown).
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, and Cool Whip; spread over cool crust.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix as it comes from the box, thawed whipped topping, undrained pineapple, marshmallows and nuts. Chill for several hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chips in pan.
Pour cereal into mixture.
Stir until cereal is all coated with chocolate. Pour all into brown paper bag.
Add generously the powdered sugar; shake well.

title: fruit cocktail ball
directions: Cream together the cream cheese with a large package of vanilla pudding.
Add fruit cocktail which has been finely chopped.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Toast the oatmeal with butter.
Form cheese mixture into ball and roll in toasted oatmeal.
Serve with cinnamon graham crackers.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix ingredients; bake for 1 or 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix all.
Let stand several hours before serving.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Put casserole in pan with 1 inch of boiling water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Carrots are cooked in boiling water like you do potatoes.

title: kindergartner's best play dough
directions: In electric skillet mix dry ingredients.
Add oil and water. Cook on low temperature approximately 3 minutes until mixture pulls away from sides.
Knead immediately.
If food color is added, knead rather than mix with liquids.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Soak dry beans and cook or just add canned beans to pot and mash the beans.
Add enough water to cover and bring to a boil. Add potatoes, peeled and diced and carrots, sliced.
Shred cabbage and kale.
Add all ingredients to beans.
Cook well and serve hot.

title: delicious buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
In large bowl mix wet ingredients (except berries).
Add dry ingredients.
Hand beat only enough to moisten.
Leave some lumps.
Cook on ungreased griddle.

title: french meat pie(tourtiere)
directions: Have butcher grind the pork and beef together, passing it through twice so it is well blended.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Microwave first four ingredients on High for 2 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Microwave for 4 more minutes.
Add baking soda. Pour over popped corn that has been put in a brown grocery bag with its inside sprayed with Pam.
Shake bag, put in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes; shake again.
Back in for 1 1/2 minutes; shake again.
Back in for 45 seconds; shake again.
Back in for 30 seconds; completed.
Put in a dish.

title: heavenly pineapple cake
directions: Cook butter, milk and sugar until bubbles, then add coconut and pecans.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar and lard and bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Add to liquid. Sift dry ingredients.
Add one cup at a time to liquid, stirring well.
If dough seems sticky, can use more flour.
Let rise 3 hours.
Knead down and put in refrigerator and use as needed.
Let rolls rise 3 hours before baking.
Will bake in 30 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Make cake according to box instructions.
In a bowl, cut up fresh strawberries and rinse thoroughly in cool tap water.
Drain. Add sugar and strawberry glaze to strawberries; mix well.
Let set for 3 hours or overnight.
After cake has been baked and cooled, spread strawberry topping across top of cake.
Cut and serve with whipped cream on top.

title: mayo cake
directions: Mix ingredients together (add soda to water to dissolve). Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased cake pan.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Top will be brown and crispy.

title: zucchini casserole with sour cream
directions: Cook zucchini in salted boiling water until tender-crisp; drain and place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large bowl and mix together. Chill well before serving.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli following directions on package.
Cook rice following directions on package.
Combine broccoli and rice.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Add milk and mix.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cut bacon slices in half.
Cut Swiss cheese into pieces the same size as bacon.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Overlap bacon and cheese slices to cover bottom of crust.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients, then add milk and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Flatten with a glass to 1/4-inch thick; chill for 30 minutes.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Dip patties; place on wax paper to harden.

title: matthew's personal pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split open muffins.
Put on cookie sheet so they don't touch.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons of tomato sauce on muffins.
Cover with cheese and add pepperoni.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool before eating.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Cut marshmallows into small pieces. Whip cream. Add marshmallows and wine or vinegar; let stand while preparing other ingredients. Crumble crackers. Add spices; mix well. Add cream and marshmallow mixture; mix well. Add nuts and chopped fruit; mix well and press in pan. Square pan works well. Cover with foil and keep refrigerated.

title: deviled english peas
directions: Arrange
a layer of peas, egg slices, pimiento and cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread half of the soup over the top. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover with onions and heat until hot.
Serves 6.

title: self-frosting date cake
directions: Mix and sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in bite size pieces.
In a large pot, lightly brown bacon.
Drain excess grease.
Add onion, garlic, mustard, ketchup, vinegar and sugar to the bacon.
Mix well.
Then add pork and beans, kidney beans (partially drained) and butter beans (completely drained).
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Cut butter into flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Mix egg into water.
Pour all at once into flour mixture and mix.
Knead on floured surface as you would for regular biscuits.
Press or roll to 1/2-inch thick and cut in 2-inch size.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Taste.
May serve as a salad, garnished with lettuce and tomato (optional) or as a sandwich.

title: volunteer cornbread
directions: Mix caring and compassion, gently blending it with community interest.
Combine time and patience with determination.
Add 1 heaping tablespoon of organization and cooperation with a dash of monetary aid and mix one pound of laughter and smiles.
Carefully fold the 3 mixtures together and pour into pan, greased generously with coordination.
Sprinkle top with human needs.
Serve proudly.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients, beginning with dry, until batter has no lumps.
Pour batter on hot buttered griddle.
Serve pancakes with a dusting of powdered sugar or syrup.

title: oven herb chicken
directions: Combine ingredients except bread crumbs and spread over chicken pieces.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place chicken, skin side up in large shallow greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Wash chops.
Place in shallow pan.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Place onion slice on top each chop.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place tomato slice on top of onion and season. Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add more water if needed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Place in greased baking dish, 3 layers, 1-inch deep.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper, flour and dot with butter. Add sliced ham between each layer.
Add milk until it can be seen between the slices of potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: *If you use instant tea with lemon in it then do not add the citric acid.

title: red beans and rice with smoked sausage
directions: Place all ingredients, except sausage and rice, in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to a simmer, cover and cook for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage to red beans the last 30 minutes of cooking time.
Serve over rice (1 cup red beans over 1 cup rice).
Serves 6.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies as directed on box, substituting 2 egg whites for whole egg, plain nonfat yogurt for oil as listed on box and amount of water as specified.
Mix as directed on box.
Spread batter in an 11 3/4-inch by 7 1/2-inch baking pan that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray on the bottom only.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, being careful not to overbake.
When cool, cut into 16 bars.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Form into ball and roll in remainder of nuts.

title: cow chip cookies
directions: Mix eggs and sugars together; add baking soda, salt, vanilla and melted butter.
Add peanut butter; add oats gradually.
Add chocolate chips, M&M's and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes bunches.

title: monkey bread
directions: Divide each biscuit into fourths and roll into balls. Roll each ball in the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Drop into a lightly greased Bundt pan.
Heat butter, brown sugar and Karo until dissolved.
Pour mixture over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool on a rack for 10 minutes and invert onto a serving plate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; add tomatoes and water and bring to boiling.
Cook for at least 20 minutes.
You can add more water if it boils down too far.

title: no fuss noodles
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and return to pan.
Add cauliflower, broccoli, soup, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Mix gently.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Place in casserole.
Combine soup, eggs, cheese, onion and mayonnaise; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix; dot with butter. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: stroganoff dip
directions: Put some oil in a heavy skillet and heat.
Break meat into very small pieces.
Add onions; sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder and flour.
Scatter over the top with the cheese, pimento, mushrooms and mushroom soup.
(Stir mushroom soup, so it can pour over top without any trouble.)
Cover tightly; cook for 20 minutes over low heat.
Do not lift lid.
When cooked, fold in the sour cream.
Add chopped fresh parsley for color.
Serve warm with your favorite crackers.
Wonderful for a group.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix 1 package dry yeast in large bowl with 2 cups lukewarm water.
Melt and add margarine.
Add egg, sugar and salt.
Add flour.
Mix good and drop by teaspoon into a greased muffin pan or you can cut out like biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: easy cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 375° oven.
After cake cools, pour over 1/2 cup orange juice or 1/2 cup rum or 1/2 cup coffee brandy.

title: parmesan bread twists
directions: Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Sprinkle both sides of each rectangle with cheese.
On unfloured surface, roll rectangles to 7 x 4-inch rectangles.
Cut each rectangle into 6 lengthwise strips.
Twist strips.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 24 twists.

title: pineapple supreme casserole
directions: Lay bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the ingredients and pour over bread.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer at least 10 minutes. Add shrimp and simmer until tender.
Serve on bed of Riceland rice.

title: weetenkamp's rivels
directions: Mix ingredients with fork or fingers until the mixture forms small crumbs.
Drop these into the soup along with the hard-cooked eggs and boil 15 minutes longer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine all other ingredients and pour into same pan butter is melted in.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Stir once after about 15 minutes.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and add the Cool Whip.
(Use fruit with no sugar and sugar-free pudding.)

title: pizza cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, water, eggs, butter and walnuts. Pour onto greased 16-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, spread with Cool Whip.

title: buttered steamed calico stew
directions: In heavy 2 quart saucepan, melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients and cover tightly.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium-low heat until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: slow cooked sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Place diced potatoes in a slow cooker, then apple juice.
In small bowl, mix apple pie filling, brown sugar, oleo and cinnamon. Spoon over potatoes.
Cover and cook on low setting for 6 to 8 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Add raisins the last half hour of cooking.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Put small amounts into blender until it turns to powder; measure first, then blend.

title: donna's crispy chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix Bisquick and pepper in large plastic bag.
Stir chicken into eggs; remove chicken with slotted spoon.
Place in bag with baking mix.
Shake bag until chicken is coated.
Remove from bag.

title: mom's fruit cobbler
directions: Blend butter and sugar well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk and mix all together.
Place fruit in bottom of 7 x 11-inch baking dish. Pour batter over fruit, then put about 1 cup sugar over batter and sprinkle water over sugar (like we used to sprinkle clothes) until sugar is wet.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Combine ground beef and flour.
Brown with onion in skillet. Stir in tomato sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Turn into an 8-inch square greased baking dish or pan.
Top with cheese and biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and biscuits are golden brown.

title: taylor's favorite gouda cheese soup
directions: Melt 3 tablespoon butter, whisk in flour.
Add stock and whisk to remove lumps.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add cheese and sour cream.
Stir until melted.
Season.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add to individual soup bowls before serving.

title: potato boats
directions: Wash and bake potatoes at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and split lengthwise.
Scrape out potatoes, leaving shells.
Mix potatoes with salt, butter and sour cream.
Spoon mixture back into shells. Add cheese to tops of potatoes.
Bake or broil until cheese is melted.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter on low heat.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add flour gradually.
Add chocolate chips and nuts or coconut.
Pour into large greased biscuit pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (no longer).
Let cool and cut in squares.
These are chewy, like brownies.

title: apple cinnamon (or banana) pancakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with whisk.
Whisk in baking powder, baking soda, then flour.
Fold in applesauce or bananas.
Add cinnamon.
Cook on a hot griddle and enjoy!
Leftovers can be frozen and reheated in the microwave.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Blend ice cream and milk.
Add 1 package of instant pudding; beat 1 minute.
Pour immediately into shell.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly combine all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in an 8-inch square dish.
Spread a layer of catsup on top of the loaf.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook at medium for 15 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in butter and salt.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix catsup, chili powder, molasses and Tabasco sauce together. Pour over any kind of meat and cook.
Great for chicken or wieners.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Add baking powder.
Beat until stiff.
Add sugar, vanilla, pecans and Ritz crackers.
Pour in greased pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Mix Cool Whip and Nestle Quik together.
Spread over cooled pie. Refrigerate.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Pour flour into bowl; add other ingredients and mix.
Put on a floured board and pat out.
(May be rolled out and cut into biscuits or you may break off pieces and roll with hands into balls.)
Pat down slightly.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: blackberry roll
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat together butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk, stirring until combined. Turn mixture into greased casserole.
Top with blackberries and sprinkle with remaining sugar.

title: chocolate butterscotch bars
directions: Add shortening to sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts, chocolate and vanilla.
Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° about 25 minutes.
While warm, cut in 50 bars.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Grate cheese; mix with margarine, salt, pepper and flour. Last, roll in Rice Krispies or pecans.
Place in teaspoon size drops on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: mushroom-stuffed deviled eggs
directions: After you hard-cook the eggs, remove shells under cold running water.
Cut eggs in half, emptying yolks into a small mixing bowl. Next, saute onions and mushrooms in a skillet using a small amount of shortening.
Mix onion and mushrooms with yolks.
Add dry mustard, parsley, lemon juice, seasoned salt, pepper and sour cream.
Using this mixture, fill the empty egg halves.
Sprinkle a little paprika over the top of each egg to give it that really professional look.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey divan casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, sour cream and curry powder.
Cut bread into bite size pieces and put in bottom of casserole.
Place cooked, drained broccoli over the bread and layer meat over it. Pour sauce on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with as much sharp cheese as you wish.
Return to oven for another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: appetizer with mushrooms
directions: Pluck stems, then add sausage and soup mix.
Stuff mushrooms. Broil 10 minutes if eaten at once.
These can be frozen, then put in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, then broiled about 5 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Put the apple cider/juice and cinnamon stick in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in the remaining ingredients except orange slices. Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Serve in punch bowl and float orange slices on top.
Makes 16 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until tender.
Cool, peel and grate coarsely.
Heat mayonnaise with soup.
Blend sour cream, onions and cheese into soup.
Stir in potatoes.

title: honey corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Combine egg, honey, margarine and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes, or until done.
Serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.

title: pickle relish
directions: Place cucumbers, bell peppers and onions in a pan and drain. Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric, cinnamon and salt and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables to vinegar mixture and heat well.
Do not boil!
Put in jars and seal.

title: fish and chips
directions: Clean fish and cut into pieces, 3 x 1 1/2-inches.
Dry on paper towel.
Beat egg yolks,
blend in beer, milk, flour and seasonings.
Mix until smooth.
Beat egg whites
until stiff, but not dry and fold in mixture.
Dip fish in batter, lift out and drain slightly.
Fry in deep fat at 375° for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Drain on paper towel.
Use rest of batter for dipping sliced potatoes and green beans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Add oil, eggs, and vanilla and blend well. Bake in 3 (9 inch) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: coffee cake
directions: Add sugar, butter and salt to hot milk.
When cool, add dissolved yeast, beaten eggs and enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise until double its size.
Cut mixture; beat thoroughly.
Spread smoothly in 2 greased round layer cake tins. Cover with second mixture.

title: aunt sally ann's tortellini appetizer(yield: appetizer for 6-10)
directions: 1. Cook tortellini and rinse under cold water when done.

title: avocado dip
directions: Slightly mash avocados.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together baking mix, egg, milk, water, vanilla, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Blend in chocolate chips.
Cook on griddle at 300° or a regular frying pan on medium-high setting. Serve with butter, syrup and whipped cream, if desired.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook the lasagna noodles.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and noodles together.
Layer in 2 - 9 x 13 pans or 1 deep dish: noodles, chicken mix and cheese.
Layer until ingredients are gone. Save some of the cheese for the top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Open can of pineapple and drain for 1 hour.
Beat cream cheese until smooth. Mix by hand the other ingredients into the cream cheese and the pineapple.
Chill in bowl several hours or overnight.
Roll in crushed pecans.
You may make 2 large balls or several small balls.
You may also freeze the balls.

title: quick crescent caramel-pecan rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown
sugar, water and pecans.
Put on bottom of the pan.
Separate each can crescent dough into 4 rectangles; seal perforations.
Spread with the 3 tablespoons of softened butter.
Combine cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over dough. Starting at shorter side, roll up each rectangle.
Cut each roll into 4 slices, forming 32 pieces.
Place, cut side down, in prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Invert immediately to remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes 32 small rolls.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Bone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Dip tortillas in hot chicken stock until wilted. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add a layer of chicken, then onion, pepper and cheese.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle garlic salt lightly over all.
Combine the two soups and the tomatoes and chilies and chili powder.
Pour over all.
(Crush the tomatoes and chilies.)
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom-bacon green beans
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: birthday punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes, then cool. Add remaining ingredients and mix together. Freeze in plastic container. When ready to serve, thaw to a slush and add 3/4 bottle of 7-Up.

title: jessie's cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Use cookie sheet.
Have a long piece of aluminum foil on counter.
In saucepan melt butter and margarine, then add brown sugar.
Stir until thick (5 to 6 minutes).
Add nuts. Line cookies (crackers) up on cookie sheet.
Put 1 teaspoon sauce on each cracker (or less).
Bake 9 minutes at 325°.
Remove from cookie sheet and place on foil to cool.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Layer and cover with crumbs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt (mixed thoroughly).
Chill dough in refrigerator (even overnight).
Roll out small portion sprinkled with flour mixed with a small portion of sugar.
Cut; place on ungreased baking sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: ultimate chocolate brownies
directions: Heat
oven
to
Grease
rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, or two square pans, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
In medium bowl combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter. Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3
cup
melted
butter; stir until smooth. Add flour, vanilla and
salt; blend completely.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into
prepared pan(s).
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until brownies begin to
pull
away from sides of pan.
Cool completely.
Frost with One-Bowl Buttercream Frosting.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: crock-pot venison
directions: Cut venison into small chunks and brown in bacon grease. Place in crock-pot.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup water.
Add bouillon and remaining ingredients to crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 12 hours.
If stew is too thin, add a few tablespoons of instant mashed potatoes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until well blended.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
(Save enough Cool Whip to decorate top if you would like to.)

title: boneless pork chops
directions: Drizzle oil on baking sheet.
Place boneless pork chops on sheet and season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add sliced hot peppers and some hot pepper juice (the hotter you like it the more peppers you use) on top of the pork chops.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes (until pork is white inside).
Just before you take it out of the oven, cover each piece with shredded cheese.
Remove from the oven when cheese has melted.

title: pilaf
directions: You will need a large frypan, medium frypan and a 6-quart pan with cover.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix coffee, sugar and boiling water.
Let cool.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Makes 1 quart.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in a large casserole dish.
Mix together flour and sugar and cut in margarine.
Sprinkle flour, sugar and margarine mixture which should look like small peas, over peaches. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Remove skin from
chicken.
Wash
each	piece and drain well. Combine flour,
herb
blend, paprika and pepper.
Place in paper or plastic bag and add 3 pieces of chicken at a time. Shake to coat.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and rosemary together until smooth; set aside.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out sugar cookie dough and follow package directions for oven temperature and time.
Cook until evenly browned.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Spread over cooled cookie.
Top with different colored fruit in different patterns.

title: roberta's homemade avocado dip
directions: Peel and mash up dark brown avocados in bowl.
Add picante sauce, stewed tomatoes, jalapeno slices and salt.
Stir all together.
Dice green onions (blade and onion head) real fine. Sprinkle over top of mixture.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips, corn chips and refried beans.

title: cooked slaw
directions: Cut cabbage fine into large bowl.
Add sliced onions and grated carrot; mix well.
Combine sugar, vinegar, corn oil, salt and mustard.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over cabbage, onions and carrot.
Put into covered container that can be stirred occasionally.
Place in refrigerator.
This makes 3 quarts and will keep a long time.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon, except the last two.
Spoon into a large pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a
crock-pot.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 hours.
Watch for scorching at the high setting.
Serve with your choice of chips; also good as a topping for hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: prune paste
directions: Prune paste replaces high fat shortening in recipes for brownies, muffins and other baked goods.
This recipe reduces the fat in recipes by at least 75%.
Best when used fresh but can be kept in the refrigerator for several days.
To make, blend the pitted prunes with the water and vanilla.

title: easy v-8 juice
directions: Tomato juice should
be hot, then add sugar and seasonings and stir well.	Process in canner.

title: lasagna manfredi
directions: Slice links thinly.
Place in skillet with garlic and 1/4 teaspoon salt; brown over high heat.
Drain on paper towel.
Set aside.

title: aunt edna's nitey-nite cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Stir in nuts and chips. Drop by teaspoon on foil covered cookie sheets.
Put in oven, close door, turn off oven and go to bed.
Awaken to great treat.

title: lebanese style rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add orzo and stir until it turns golden brown.
Add rinsed, drained rice and stir and brown slightly.
Add water and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil, then cover and put on a very low heat for about 15 to 20 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: party punch (slush)
directions: Mix box of jello with hot water.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Take out 1 hour before party.
Add 1 liter ginger ale when thawed enough to stir.
Stir again 15 minutes before served.
Makes a slush.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring to a boil 1 cup of water.
Add cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until fork-tender.
Refrigerate potatoes until cold (approximately 1 hour).
Peel and grate cold potatoes.
Add sour cream, 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese, scallions, salt and pepper.
Put mixture in buttered casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Chill for several hours.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes. Garnish with chives or chopped green scallion tops, if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Great for crowds.
Easy to make ahead of time!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into baking dish. Cover top with ketchup and bake at 400° until done.

title: chinese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo; cool five minutes.
Stir sugar into oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add the other contents and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix together.
Grease and flour pans.
You may use 5 one-layer pans or 1 tube pan.
For the layer pans, bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
For the tube pan bake at 300° for 60 minutes.

title: kringles
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and vanilla.
Put the soda in the sour cream and buttermilk; add the egg mixture.
Add the sifted dry ingredients.
Chill well.
Roll in long rolls and form into bows or pretzel shapes.
Bake in a hot oven at 350° until brown or paler, if you prefer.

title: shrimp and tortellini
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat; add shrimp, minced shallot and basil.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pasta and cheese.
Toss gently; add fresh basil as garnish, if desired. Serves 4.

title: breakfast pizza(serves 6 or more)
directions: Cook sausage.
Break rolls into a pizza pan (round) forming a circle.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Lay drained sausage on crescents, spreading sausage.
Mix beaten eggs, milk and oregano until fluffy.
Add pepper and pour over sausage.
Mix cheeses and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coca-cola baked chicken
directions: Line baking pan with foil.
Salt and pepper the chicken.
Place in pan.
Pour the Coke and ketchup over the chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
If you want it browned, remove foil about 15 minutes before removing from oven.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish and top with 1/2 cup cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: slaw
directions: Wash vegetables and apples; drain.
Cut cabbage into shreds with a knife.
Cube unpeeled apples.
Cut broccoli flowerets and peel upper stem and chop.
Shred carrots with grater.
Add cole slaw dressing to taste.
Let stand a few minutes at room temperature before tossing.
If not to be eaten immediately, cover with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator.
Eat within 2 days.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Cook noodles in salt water.
Mix all together in baking dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix well at low speed.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degree.
Grease pie plate or pan (9 or 10 inch).
Place all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend on high speed 16 seconds.
Pour into pie pan and bake 50 to 55 minutes or until tooth pick inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars with 1 head of dill and 1 clove of garlic in each jar.
Put vinegar, water and salt in large kettle and bring to a boil.
Pour while boiling hot over cucumbers in jars.
Cover each jar with canning lid and ring.
Place jars in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
(Start timing as soon as jars are placed in boiling water.)
Makes 7 quarts.

title: oven-baked potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes in 1/2-inch slices.
Alternate sliced potatoes and onions in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle margarine. Sprinkle garlic powder, salt, pepper and celery seed. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with paprika and bake an additional 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat until blended.
Add vanilla and stir in dates, nuts and coconut.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir well while still hot; cool.
Form into small balls and dip in sugar.

title: boston nut bread
directions: Chop dates and nuts.
Put into bowl with butter and baking soda and pour over 1 cup boiling water.
Let stand until cool. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt and beat well.
Stir in flour and add ingredients from other bowl.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese slices and Tater Tots or sliced potatoes.
Put cheese slices and Tater Tots or sliced potatoes on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugar until light.
Beat in eggs. Combine banana and milk.
Mix in soda and salt.
Alternately blend in dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir and let stand or set 3 hours.
Next day, wash sauerkraut good and squeeze dry.
Add all vegetables.
Put in covered dish and set overnight.

title: aunt jess' chicken
directions: Put rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and water and pour over rice.
Sprinkle 1 package Lipton soup over.
Lay chicken in pan. Sprinkle the other package of soup over.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Check at 1 1/2 hours to see if dry enough.
If it isn't, take cover off and continue to bake.

title: warm cabbage salad
directions: In large serving bowl, combine cabbage and carrots.
Set aside.

title: very easy fruit cocktail cake
directions: Pour fruit cocktail in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the fruit cocktail.
Take slices of the butter and put on top of cake mix.
Make sure you place slices all over the top so butter may melt evenly into cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Great served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: vegetable soup(approximately 3 quarts)
directions: Brown meat.
Put oil in skillet and brown stew meat, then drain.
Add beef broth, tomatoes, beef bouillon cubes, meat, onion, cabbage, bay leaves, carrots, celery and water, everything but mixed vegetables, potatoes and macaroni.
Gently boil until carrots begin to get tender, then add potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Melt margarine and brown onion.
Add sausage and garlic to brown.
Stir in flour and cook thoroughly.
Add broth, sauerkraut and parsley; cook few minutes more, until stiff.
Chill.
Roll into bite-size balls and chill again (or freeze until ready to use).

title: sour cream drops
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add sour cream, and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well and chill at least 1 hour.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mother's oatmeal bread
directions: Stir together in large mixer bowl, boiling water, rolled oats, shortening, brown sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm, then dissolve yeast in warm water and add yeast, eggs and 1/2 flour to lukewarm mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl frequently.
Add rest of flour and mix with spoon until flour is thoroughly blended into dough.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic and quits being sticky.
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and then shape into 3 loaves.
Place in 3 greased pans. Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. When baked, brush tops with butter.

title: apricot pecan salad
directions: Place pineapple, including juice, in a 4-cup glass measure. Microwave on High until bubbly hot, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Cut cream cheese into large chunks and add to pineapple mixture.
Stir midway through cooking, then microwave on Medium (50%) until cheese is completely softened to blend into mixture, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in apricots.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in 1/4 cup nuts and Cool Whip.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top as garnish. Refrigerate until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lettuce and mayonnaise salad
directions: Shred lettuce in 2-quart dish 3/4 full.
Drain peas and spread over top.
Chop celery and spread over peas.
Spread Hellmann's mayonnaise over top and sprinkle sugar and Parmesan cheese on top. Top with onion rings.

title: never fail vegetable beef sour
directions: Put juice, tomatoes, bouillon, onion, celery, water and meat in crock-pot early in the morning.
If you're home during the day, stir occasionally.
Cook on low.
An hour or so before serving, parboil veggies; drain and add to soup.
Good soup, better the next day.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until macaroni is tender. Yield: 4 servings.

title: apple crisp(350~ for 45 minutes)
directions: Place
apples
in
bottom
of greased baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar,
baking
powder,
salt and egg with a fork until crumbly. Place
on top of the apples.
Pour 1/4 cup of melted and
cooled shortening on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kielbasa and vegetables
directions: Fry bacon over medium-high heat until crispy.
Remove from pan.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows in a double boiler and heat until marshmallows are completely melted. Add cracker crumbs to marshmallow cream and mix well. Then add all other ingredients, mixing well. Put in a Bundt pan or pound cake pan lined with plastic wrap. Pour mixture into lined pan and press mixture into pan. Refrigerate for 2 days.

title: red button's cheesy chewies(for cats)
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly in medium bowl.
Drop 1/2 teaspoonful at a time onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 8 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Cool to room temperature and store in airtight container in refrigerator, freeze for longer storage.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon and hamburger with onion.
Mix other ingredients and pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: cold spiced carrots
directions: Briefly cook the carrot coins by the desired method.
Drain well and mix with raw onions and pepper strips.
Place in a nonmetallic bowl with lid.
Use a wire whisk and electric blender or food processor to combine soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate overnight. Makes 10 servings.

title: cheddar broccoli casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly
soup and milk.
Arrange broccoli in 8 x 12-inch
casserole.
Layer
eggs,
can fried onions, soup mixture and
cheese
over
broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: hannah's fresh corn salad
directions: Cook the fresh corn for 3 minutes in a salted pot of boiling water. Drain the corn and immerse it in ice water to stop the cooking and set the color. When the corn is cool, cut the kernels off the cob, cutting close to the cob. Toss the kernels in a large bowl with red onions, vinegar, olive oil, salt and pepper. Right before serving, toss in the fresh basil. Serve cold or at room temperature. Only use fresh corn, not frozen.

title: fried potatoes and then some
directions: Fry potatoes in butter (margarine okay).
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Sprinkle to cover lightly the Salad Supreme.
When potatoes are almost ready, add onions and sausage. Turn often.
Cover until sausage is heated.
Serve with favorite veggie.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Sprinkle pork with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in wok or skillet over moderately high heat.
Add half the pork.
Cook 3 to 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cook through, remove from wok, repeat with remaining pork.
Reduce heat to moderately low.
Mix pineapple juice and cornstarch and set aside.

title: don't peek chicken
directions: Place uncooked rice in a baking dish.
Add chicken.
Combine soups with 1/2 can of milk and pour over.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix on top.
Seal securely and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours. Don't peek in!

title: cream broccoli soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, onion, broccoli and all the seasonings together.
Omit flour, milk and margarine at this time.
Cook broccoli, chicken broth, onion and seasonings to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Put vegetable mixture in blender until creamy.
Set aside.
In same pan melt butter.
Add salt and flour; stir until smooth.
Then add milk until thickens.
Add to broccoli mixture until heated.
Add 1 cup broccoli florets.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with fork.
Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with chips or over Mexican food.
Great on tacos.

title: grilled oriental sweets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; stir well and set aside.
Arrange potato wedges in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 10 minutes.
Place on platter and brush cut sides with oil.

title: six cup salad
directions: Combine coconut, marshmallows, pineapple, oranges and blueberries in bowl; mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, flour, sugar and margarine together.
Add milk and spices.
Taste.
Add more milk, sugar or spices, if needed.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook chicken; remove skin and bone and cut in small pieces. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles and rinse with cold water.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Serve as soon as done or chill before serving.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix well.
Roll chicken in flour and brown.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken and cover.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until sauce is thick.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix in pan strawberries and sugar.
Cook these together until sugar is dissolved, then add Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Chill.
Whip milk.
Mix chilled ingredients and milk together; pour into a cooled baked pie shell.

title: pineapple glazed carrots
directions: In a saucepan, combine all the ingredients except the carrots. Bring the mixture to a boil.
Lower the heat, add the carrots and simmer until the liquid is absorbed.
Season with salt and pepper. Cook for several minutes more, shaking the pan until slices are glazed.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook egg yolks, Carnation milk and sugar; let cool.
Whip the cream; add cooked egg mixture.
Drain pineapple and add with rest of the ingredients.
Chill.

title: chilled cherry soup
directions: Combine in a large pot the contents of 2 cans of cherries, plus only the cherries from the other 2 cans.
Add lemon and spices (tied up in a cloth) plus sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil. Blend flour and cream with a whisk.
Add this to cherry mixture. Add wine.
Bring it all again to a boil.
Cool and then refrigerate for 4 hours or more.
Serve with dollop of whipped cream, if desired.
Will keep covered in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: stuffed sole
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion, shrimp and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender.
Add crabmeat; heat through.
Sprinkle fillets with salt, pepper and paprika.
Spoon crabmeat mixture on fillets; roll up and fasten with a toothpick.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cocido
directions: Boil short ribs in 1 1/2-quarts water.
Skim.
When the meat is tender, add tomatoes, onion and vegetables.
Add vegetables that need longer cooking time first.
Add in this order: carrots, turnips, potatoes, celery, corn and cabbage.
Add salt to taste. Serve the dark clear broth on the side and the vegetables on a platter.
Diners can mix their own caldillo or eat the soup and vegetables separately.

title: peanut patties
directions: Boil first five ingredients on low to medium heat for 1 hour. Remove from heat and add remaining three ingredients. Beat by hand until thick. Drop by spoon fulls on wax paper. Let cool.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Dice chicken and place in the baking dish.
Mix together the soup and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle crackers over mixture.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed and bake at 350° until brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over the cream cheese.
Chill.

title: apple roll-ups
directions: Chop
apples.
Roll pastry 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with melted butter and cinnamon-sugar.
Add chopped apples and roll as a jelly roll.
Cut
in
slices
1 1/4 inches thick.
Place slices in greased baking pan 1-inch apart.
Cover with syrup. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Delicious served hot with rich milk.

title: leah's crunchy punch
directions: Bring 9 cups of water to a boil; add jello.
In another boiler, bring 4 cups water and sugar to a boil.
Mix sugar mixture into jello mixture and let cool.
Divide this mixture into two 1-gallon ice cream buckets.
When cool, add 1/2 bottle lemon juice and 1 can pineapple juice to each bucket.
Freeze this. Take out 1 hour before you plan to serve.
Chop it up into large chunks and add 2 quarts cold 7-Up over this and slush it up. Serve slushy.
Serves 75.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt oleo. Stir in milk, vanilla and salt. Mix well. Remove from heat. Add 3 1/2 cups powdered sugar gradually until smooth. Add peanut butter and syrup. Mix well. Turn out onto board sprinkled with remaining sugar. Knead until consistency of play dough. Form into small balls. Melt chips and shortening in double boiler. Remove from heat. Dip balls, using toothpick to cover 3/4 of the way. Place on waxed paper until set. Store in refrigerator. Yields 100 balls.

title: mettie's coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, mini chocolate chips, cinnamon and nuts in a bowl and set aside.
Place cake mix, sour cream and oil in a bowl. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
In a tube pan, place 1/3 of the batter and add 1/2 of the nut mixture.
Top the nut mixture with another 1/3 of the batter, then add the other half of the nuts and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Saute onions and sliced sausage in oil until onions are transparent and sausage is browned.
Add all other ingredients, including bean liquid to a large pot.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for about 45 minutes until potatoes are cooked.
Serves 4.

title: basic bakers clay dough for tree ornaments
directions: Mix flour and salt with spatula or wooden spoon.
Add water slowly, mixing as you pour.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Dough should be soft and smooth.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut shapes for Christmas tree decorations.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.
May color dough with food coloring or paint ornaments before baking.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix flour, Parmesan cheese and salt in a bowl.
Melt butter. Peel and cut potatoes into wedges; drain.
Dip in butter, then coat in cheese mixture.
Bake in dish at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 more minutes.
May add more butter and parsley flakes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with hands.
Put in the refrigerator a few minutes before rolling into small balls.
Bake in 300° oven until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot and again when cold.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Top with melted butter and cracker crumbs combined.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: uncooked candy
directions: Mix sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Add cream and mix until dough can be formed.
Roll out on sugared board and spread with peanut butter.
Roll over and slice into pinwheels.

title: sherried black bean soup
directions: In a 3-quart Dutch oven, cook carrots, onion and garlic in hot oil over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add cumin and cook until carrots are tender.
Stir in the beans (drained), ham, sherry, bouillon granules, bay leaves, oregano and red pepper with 6 cups of water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Make balls size of walnuts; roll in sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a soft, but firm ball.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Return balance of syrup to fire and continue cooking until it forms a very hard ball.
Pour into egg white mixture and continue beating. Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until very stiff.
Pour in lightly buttered platter.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: marshall field sandwich
directions: For each sandwich:
Take 3 pieces beef steak rye and remove crusts.
Butter the bread.
Layer bread, lettuce, ham, tomato, bread, ham, 3 strips bacon, bread and hard-boiled egg (crumbled).

title: tex-mex fiesta bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare stuffing using water and margarine.
Spoon into bottom of greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish Combine onion, pepper, chicken, tomato, corn and picante sauce. Spoon over stuffing.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cover with cheese and bake 10 minutes.

title: potato balls
directions: Place potatoes in casserole and add water and butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle parsley over top.
Cover and bake at 375° until potatoes are tender.

title: honey sesame tenderloin
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and oil.
Place tenderloins in this marinade overnight in refrigerator.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix together and let set 4 hours to let bubbles settle.

title: eggplant sticks
directions: Peel and slice eggplant into finger size pieces.
Soak in sugared ice water 30 minutes and drain.

title: beef and fresh broccoli soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until beef is tender. Remove bay leaves.
Add water and mushrooms.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add broccoli.
Simmer for 4 minutes.
Add squash. Simmer 3 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: mushroom parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and remove mushroom stems.
Chop the stems and mix with garlic, parsley, cheese, oregano, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Place mushroom stem side up in baking dish.
Fill mushrooms with mixture.
Add 1/4 inch of water to dish. Pour olive oil evenly over caps and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix
together
brown
sugar,
soft shortening, milk and eggs. Add
remaining ingredients.
Dip with a small ice cream dipper. Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry crush cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pour the rest of the soda over cake while still hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown turkey and onion, then drain.
Mix everything together. Simmer for about 1 hour or until sauce is thick.
Add water if not enough liquid after cooking.
Add bacon for extra taste (optional).

title: sweet and sour chicken wings or pork or beef ribs
directions: Brown chicken wings in hot shortening.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Drain drippings from skillet and add vinegar, sugar, pineapple juice, catsup, soy sauce, mustard and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Then boil gently 5 minutes.
Add browned wings.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet onto serving dish over rice, if you like.
Serves four.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put dry ingredients in a large bowl, then mix in liquids. (This prevents the starch from clumping.)
Dip ribs in marinade, then let soak for 8 hours or overnight.

Bake for 30 minutes at 325°, pour off fat, turn ribs over and bake for 20 minutes more. Pour off fat, brush with a mixture of duck sauce and Chinese mustard; broil until it sizzles, flip, brush, broil and devour.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip on serving plate.
In a small bowl, mash the avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper; spread over bean dip. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, and taco seasoning; spread over the avocado layer.
Sprinkle with cheese, olives, onions and tomato. Serve with chips.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt margarine with sugar and milk in a pan.
Let boil on medium heat for approximately 10 minutes or until you can drop a little into a cold glass of water and it stays together as in a ball at the bottom of glass.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter. Stir in and refrigerate.

title: delicious macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer baking dish with macaroni, ham, onion and sliced Velveeta cheese, ending with Velveeta cheese.
Pour evaporated milk over casserole.
Dot with a small amount of butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Make jello using cola instead of cold water. Add nuts, pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Place in refrigerator to set up. Should be stirred before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: If using the raw cranberries, grind and add sugar.
Let stand for at least an hour.
Mix plain gelatin mixture with the lemon gelatin.
Let the mixture begin to congeal before adding the ingredients.
When the process begins, add the cranberries and nuts.
Also add celery.
Add pineapple and orange juice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line pie plate with pie crust.
Boil sugar and syrup together for about 2 minutes.
Pour over slightly beaten eggs, stirring vigorously.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: aunt babes' chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa mix in margarine until crumbly.
Reserving 2 cups crumb mix, press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Beat cheese until fluffy.
Mix in Eagle Brand, egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour over crust.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Stir everything together. Drop pieces of candy onto wax paper. Chill candy for a short time around 20 minutes. Ready to eat.

title: meatball yummies
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and 2 teaspoons steak sauce. Mix and shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in oil.
Drain fat. Combine 1/3 cup steak sauce, brown sugar and butter.
Add meatballs.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Crumble and cook meat in salad oil with garlic salt until fairly well done.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes and seasonings and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
At same time cook noodles in boiling salt water; when tender, drain and rinse.
Fill baking dish with alternate layers of noodles, sliced Muenster cheese, cottage cheese, meat sauce and grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 370°.
This casserole can be made well ahead of time, then heated just before serving.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix into crumbs.
When cake is done, put crumbs on top and bake for 10 more minutes.
Cake is especially good when crumbs are doubled in amount.
Cool, then add powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: rocky road candy
directions: Add the 3 ingredients together and stir.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and let set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients except broccoli and crushed Cheez-Its.
Add broccoli and pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with Cheez-Its and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add pineapple and cheese.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pork barbecue sandwiches
directions: In Dutch oven, combine meat and water.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 3/4 to 2 1/4 hours or until meat is very tender.
Remove meat from broth; reserve 1/2 cup broth.
Return broth to saucepan and add onion and celery.
Cook, covered, for about 10 minutes or until veggies are very tender. Stir in brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Remove meat from bones and discard fat and bones.
Chop or shred remaining meat.
Add meat to mixture in saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for about 10 minutes or until the texture is desired consistency. Serve on buns.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 1,000 island dressing
directions: Mix all of ingredients and taste.
Can add more chili sauce and pickle relish.
Add a little salt and pepper.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs and brown in shortening.
Remove hot dogs from pan and saute onions with chili powder until tender.
Stir in soup and water and mix well.
Add hot dogs back to soup mixture and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: corn dip
directions: Chill for 4 hours serve.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in peanut butter and chocolate chips. Add Rice Chex until coated evenly.
Spread on a cookie sheet and cool.
Shake on powdered sugar just to cover lightly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Add flour and stir.
Add drained corn and carton of whipping cream.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Roll in corn flakes.
Put in casserole dish and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Pour into well-greased 11 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Cover top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: sticky buns
directions: Lightly grease a bundt cake pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Mix butter, cinnamon and brown sugar in sauce pan until it begins to bubble.
Pour on top of rolls.
Cover with foil and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed apples(these are baked apples with a surprise)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Core the apples, being careful not to break through the blossom end (the bottom).
Place a date in the cored center of each apple, then place 1/2 teaspoon each of sugar, butter and walnuts on top of the date.
Arrange apples in baking dish.
Sprinkle with water and bake, basting frequently, for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add pepper, salt, onion and rice. Cover with rice; let cook until rice is done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pupu meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
With damp hands, form into 1-inch balls.
Fry in small amount of fat until brown and cooked. Serve on toothpicks with dipping sauce, equal amounts of cranberry sauce and tomato ketchup that have been heated together.

title: mama's banana pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except bananas and vanilla wafers. Layer cookies, bananas and pudding mixture.
(You can use condensed milk instead of sour cream.)
I usually half the recipe.

title: five bean salad
directions: Shake well and pour over beans.
Chill overnight.

title: bonnie's pineapple salad
directions: 1st Layer:
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water and 1 can drained, crushed pineapple.
Save juice for 3rd Layer, 1 1/3 cups.
Put into long dish and let set completely.

title: rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening; cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in water.
When milk has cooled put in large bowl and add yeast mixture.
Add enough flour to make stiff batter.
Put onto cloth and work enough flour in to make soft dough.
Grease bowl large enough to let dough rise.
Place dough in it and let rise 1 hour or until double in bulk.
Put back on floured cloth, punch down (do not add flour).
Form in rolls, butter tops.
Place on baking sheet.
Let rise until double (1 hour).
Bake 15 minutes in 450° oven.
Pan rolls, like biscuits; clover leaf, 3 small balls in muffin pans.
Parker House, roll dough out round, brush melted butter, fold in half.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Beat egg in bowl; add oil.
In separate bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to egg mixture.
Add sugar, salt and flour. Mix well.
Let rise 1 hour, then make into rolls.
Place rolls in greased pan.
Let rolls rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: no sugar chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add hot water, shortening, syrup and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jello 7-up cake
directions: Make cake mix in two layers and cool.
Place plastic wrap on 2 plates and place cooled cakes on top of plastic wrap.
Put holes in cakes with fork.
Mix 1 package Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water. Add 1 cup cold 7-Up.
Pour this mixture over the cake layer, using plastic wrap to get mixture onto side of cake.
Repeat with second box of Jell-O.
Chill until firm.
Frost with Cool Whip at the last minute.
Makes a cool, light dessert.
I use cherry and lime Jell-O at Christmas.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Boil
together	shrimp,
celery tops, salt and pickling spices 10
to
minutes.
Drain;
clean and devein shrimp. Alternate in	13
x 9-inch glass pan shrimp and onion slices. Add 7 to 8 bay leaves.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 3/4 stick of melted butter in a deep baking dish.
Do not stir!
Add 2 pints of peaches mixed with 3/4 cup sugar.
Do not stir!
Bake 1 hour at 350° on lowest oven rack.

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Cook rice.
Pour
rice	in large bowl.	Add soups;
mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mixture will be very juicy.
Cut
up
chicken
and
place skin side up on rice mixture. Add salt
and pepper to taste.
Do not cover.
Place in 350° oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cinnamon french toast
directions: Prepare apples and French toast the day before.
In large skillet, melt butter and cook apples slices over medium heat.
Stir occasionally until tender.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and cinnamon to apples.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly.
Add bread in 1 layer on top. In bowl, beat eggs, milk and vanilla with fork.
Pour mixture over apples and bread.
Cover and refrigerate all overnight.
In the morning, place in 375° preheated oven.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. When firm and gold, remove from oven and cool 5 minutes.
Invert on serving tray so apples are on top.
Spoon any left in pan over bread.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Crumble up toast and put in baking dish; pour over this the pineapple.
Mix eggs, sugar and margarine; pour over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs or croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead well with hands.
Roll into small little fingers.
Drop into salted boiling water. Remove when dumplings surface and put in pan with melted margarine.

title: garlic ripe olives
directions: Drain olives.
To olives, add mixture of other ingredients. Cover and chill.
Serve.
Save liquid and use for salad dressing.

title: noodle dish
directions: Brown meat, onion
and
celery.
Add
other ingredients (except cheese) and cook on
top of stove (covered) or in 350° oven until noodles are
done.
Add cheese and continue cooking until it has melted (about 5 minutes).

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg; boil noodles and drain.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, put layer of noodles, then layer of browned hamburg, then layer of noodles, layer of cottage cheese, etc., until all ingredients are used.
Finish with layer of noodles and cut up sausage, if desired. Pour spaghetti sauce over this and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Quick and easy.

title: strawberry gravy
directions: Puree strawberries and juice with cornstarch.
Pour into pot and heat until thickened.
May need to add more cornstarch, if too thin.
Serve over hot biscuits or pancakes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: multi-purpose mix
directions: In large bowl or pot, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut shortening into flour mixture until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Store airtight in cool, dry place.
Use within 3 months.
Makes 13 cups. For whole wheat mix, substitute 5 cups whole wheat flour for 5 cups of the all-purpose flour.
Works well with either mix.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Put half of ingredients in crock-pot in layers; sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers and pour soup over top.
Season with pepper and paprika to taste.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until done.

title: another squash casserole
directions: *One package frozen squash can be substituted for fresh squash.

title: veal or chicken piccata
directions: Slice cutlets thin.
Place in flour, then egg.
Fry in hot oil in skillet until lightly golden.
Have another pan slowly simmering with melted butter.
Drain well from oil and place in butter. Simmer a few minutes.
Squeeze juice of 1/2 ot 1 lemon over cutlets.
Try not to cook too much, that butter burns.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve, spooning lemon-butter sauce over cutlets. Enjoy!

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all ingredients in a crock-pot. Cook on low all day and chow down.

title: best yum - uh - rum cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good isn't it?
Now proceed.
