Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right!
To be sure the rum is of the highest quality, pour 1 cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat!
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 seaspoon of tugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure that the rum is of the finest quality.
Try another cup.
Open the second quart, if necessary. Add 2 earge 1eggs and 2 cups fried druit; beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in the beaters, just pry it loose with a drewscriber.
Check that rum again.
Next sift 3 cups of pepper or salt (it doesn't matter).
Sample the rum again.
Sift 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Fold in bhopped cuttermilk and add strained nuts. Add 1 bablespoon of srown tugar or whatever color you can find. Wix mell.
Grease oven and turn on cake pan to 350 gredees.
Now pour the whole mess into the oven.
Oops!!!
Oh, forget the cake. Check the rest of the rum.
Forget the oven mess.
Check the rum again.
Have a nice rest.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly and put into pie shell (save a small amount for the top of the pie).
Mix together in a saucepan the flour, sugar and salt. Gradually stir in 2 cups milk.
Cook over medium heat or use a double boiler, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and gradually stir in about half of the hot mixture into the 2 beaten egg yolks.
Then blend into the hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil one minute more. Remove from heat and add oleo and vanilla.
Pour filling into the baked pie shell and let cool.
Spread top with prepared Dream Whip and sprinkles of peanut butter mixture. Serve chilled.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Spread on cake, then brown under broiler for a few minutes.

title: polish beet soup
directions: Simmer soup meat and bay leaves for about 1 1/2 hours. Grate or rice the beets, then add to stock along with onions. Turn off heat and add vinegar and sugar. Serve plain or may add cream. To prevent curdling of cream, temper it by adding 1 cup of hot soup to the cream slowly, stirring constantly. Then add this to remaining soup.

title: no-knead whole wheat bread
directions: Combine 1 cup warm water and dry yeast and let stand 5 minutes.
Add honey, oil, salt, 3 cups warm water and flour.
Stir together.
It will be stiff, but can be stirred with a spoon. Grease well 3 loaf pans 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inches.
Divide into pans. Put in oven and turn on for 1 minute at 350°.
Turn oven off and let rise 15 minutes.
Turn oven on again to 350° and bake 50 minutes.
Let bread stand about 10 minutes after removing from oven.
Turn out onto wire rack and let cool.

title: steak fingers
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Beat egg and milk together. Roll steak in milk and egg mixture.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and flour.
Roll steak strips in crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt; fry.

title: southwestern sausage turnovers
directions: Mince the cilantro or parsley.
In a food processor, combine the flour, cornmeal, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and half of the cilantro or parsley.
Add the butter and shortening; pulse until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add the ice water, a tablespoon at a time, until the dough forms a cohesive mass. Divide the dough into 6 portions; flatten each into a disk.
Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate until chilled, at least 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch cheese cake
directions: Melt morsels and butter.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese.
Add Eagle Brand milk, egg and vanilla until smooth; pour over crust.
Add remaining crust and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: no bake chow mein candy
directions: Melt chips thoroughly. Add noodles. Drop by tsp. on waxed paper and cool.

title: jimmy's cheese things
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients together. Roll into quarter-sized balls. Mash each ball with a fork to depress into a cookie shape. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes approximately 100.

title: california pumpkin raisin bread
directions: Mix well oil, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Add pumpkin, water and spices; blend well.
In another bowl, mix flour, soda and raisins.
No sifting necessary and this coats the raisins so they stay moist.
Add this to creamed mixture and pour
evenly into 4 (1 pound size) greased coffee cans or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool upright for 15 minutes.
Remove from cans and let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add egg, water and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and soda; beat until smooth.
Add chocolate chips into mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: mocha meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, adding salt, sugar, vanilla and vinegar gradually while beating. Spread 2 squares of meringue on two 6 x 9-inch pieces of brown paper. Bake at 275° for 1 hour or longer.
When done, it will lift off paper easily. Bake at lowest level in the oven. Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Take off heat and add enough cold water gradually to make chocolate drop off end of spoon. Whip the cream. Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and 1 teaspoon instant coffee.
Spread half of the chocolate mixture on meringue.
Spread a layer of half the cream mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped walnuts. Stack second meringue on top and repeat layer. Chill at least 8 hours.

title: 1-2-3-4 layer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Add flavorings and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: michigan navy bean and potato soup
directions: Rinse dry beans.
In Dutch oven or 3-quart saucepan, combine beans and water.
Cover pan and let stand in cool place overnight. (Or bring to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover, let stand for 1 hour and drain.)
Add 7 1/2 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook, covered, over medium heat for 1 hour or until beans are nearly tender.
Add potato, onion, catsup, carrot, salt, pepper and ham (omit salt if ham is added).
Return mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until beans and vegetables are tender.
Mash beans and vegetables slightly, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding and corn syrup.
Add milk and eggs, beat well, add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm and top cracks (about 40 minutes).
Cool.
Serve with cool whip, if desired.

title: deviled steak strips
directions: Cut beef into thin strips about 2 inches long and coat with flour.
In treated skillet, brown meat, onion and garlic.
Stir in 1 cup water, tomato sauce, vinegar, horseradish, mustard and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour (or until meat is tender); stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup water, scraping browned bits from bottom of pan; heat through.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in freezer.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Batter will be very stiff.
Press batter into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into 2-inch squares.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Sift remaining ingredients together and add.
Chill dough; roll into walnut-size balls.
Dip in sugar and sprinkle with 2 or 3 drops of water; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until set, but not hard, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until well blended. Add pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
Cook in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thick, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Stir into hot mixture until dissolved.
Cool. Beat egg whites until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form. Fold into the filling. Pour mixture into crust. Chill. Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch and add boiling water.
Cook over medium heat until thick and add Jell-O.
Put strawberries in a baked pie shell.
Pour cooked mixture over berries.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: salsa cream dip
directions: Press cream cheese evenly on platter.
Spread salsa sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Microwave on Medium-high for 2 1/2 minutes or until center is warm.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, paprika and salt.
Add honey, lemon juice, vinegar and onion juice.
Pour into blender.
Cover and blend on high for 1 minute.
Continue to blend on high as oil is poured slowly through opening in cover.
Stop the blender.
Stir in poppy seed.
Refrigerate.
Yields 1 pint.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast dissolved in warm water.
Mix until moistened. Cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready for use.
Cut with biscuit cutter and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt, and soda; blend well.
Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs.
Mix well.
Spoon half of the batter into a greased, heated heavy skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese and chili peppers.
Cover with remaining cornbread mixture. Bake at 375 degree for 35 or 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma's gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Add gumdrops last.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cut when cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: crunchy cabbage
directions: Wash vegetables thoroughly.
Cut cabbage crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.
Place in a skillet after adding the melted margarine, or your choice of fat.
Cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes, uncovered.
Turn cabbage over and top with crosswise slices of bell pepper.
Cover and cook for an additional 3 to 5 minutes and serve with bell pepper atop the cabbage.
Yields approximately 4 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and jello.
Add well beaten eggs, oil and water; mix well.
Add 1/2 cup strawberries, mostly berries. Bake at 325°.
Let cake cool completely before frosting.

title: butter pecan coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package, using 2 tablespoons less water.
Pour 1/2 of batter in tube pan.
Mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half on top of batter.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: microwave cabbage and potato bake
directions: In microwave-safe 2-quart casserole dish, combine potatoes and water. Cover and microwave on High power for 8 to 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once during cooking.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes.
Drain.
In 1 1/2-quart dish, combine milk and margarine.
Microwave, uncovered, on High power 1 minute. Mash potatoes and blend in hot milk mixture with salt and pepper. Place onion and garlic in the 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave, uncovered, on High power for 1 to 2 minutes or until onion is soft.
Stir in cabbage.
Cover and microwave on High power 7 to 12 minutes or until cabbage is tender, stirring once while cooking. Stir in mashed potatoes. Cover and microwave on High power 2 to 3 minutes to heat through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, corn syrup, chocolate and milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball forms when small amount is dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat and let cool.

title: vidalia chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken meat, onion, grapes, and almonds in a large mixing bowl.
In a small bowl mix together mayonnaise, dry mustard, and curry powder.
Toss with chicken mixture to coat thoroughly.
Chill at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: pie crust cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt; add shortening as for pie crust.
Add egg, sugar, sour or buttermilk, raisins and seasonings and beat well.
Bake in a 375° oven slowly.

title: chicken pasta parmesan
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Remove and set aside.

In drippings, cook mushrooms and onion. Add sherry and soup. Heat through stirring often. Add chicken and peppers. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir occasionally. Stir in cheese until melted. Serve over noodles.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut pepper in half lengthwise.
Place pepper in pan.
In a medium size bowl, crumble beef.
Add rice, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic, water, egg and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Add remaining tomato sauce over pepper and cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Use fork.
Mix together cheese, sausage and Bisquick.
Form in balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: These rolls are very easy and need no kneading.

title: impossible ham and swiss pie
directions: Spray 9-inch pie plate with Pam.
Sprinkle in meat, cheese and onion. Blend rest of ingredients (lumpy).
Pour over meat, cheese and onions.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain liquids from 3 cans of beans and rinse.
Place beans in large bowl.
Slice onion and cut pepper into small pieces; add to beans.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients; pour over bean mixture.
Refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo until onion is clear. Add rice. Add soup, milk, cheese and broccoli. Add chicken.
Put into 2-quart dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Over medium heat, heat chicken broth, chicken, noodles, carrots, onion, celery, dill weed and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, simmer about 20 minutes or until chicken and noodles are cooked.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Make a paste of vinegar, cocoa and food coloring; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Pour into three 10-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash potatoes well, then cut each in half lengthwise, then into 1/4 to 1/8-inch wedges.
Place wedges, slightly overlapping, in a single layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Brush potatoes with half of the oil mixture and bake, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done and light golden, basting occasionally with the remaining oil mixture.

title: anita's shrimp dish couvillion
directions: Use shrimp that we order from the hospital.
This feeds about 35 to 40 people.
Cook a pot of rice and set aside.
Cut up celery, bell pepper, regular onion and green onion.
I call this trinity.

In a large saucepan, after you have melted butter, make a layer of trinity and a layer of shrimp (seasoned with Tony's and garlic powder, you may add some cayenne pepper if you want it hot) and sprinkle flour or cornstarch over this.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook until the shrimp are done.
Serve over rice.
Do not let it stick.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all ingredients but sour cream. Cool and add sour cream.
Bake in greased casserole 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat sugar and oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 3 unbaked 9 inch pie shells.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: spicy spaghetti
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients for meatballs.
Shape into balls. Brown in small amount of oil in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients to meatballs in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve over spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.

title: cream pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over low heat until thick; stir constantly.
Add cornstarch mixed with water.
Pour pie ingredients into 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: eggplant soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
(Don't let it stick.)
Add eggplant and 1 cup water.
Add next 5 ingredients. Boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until eggplant is tender.
Add tomato sauce and another cup of water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Dip pieces of chicken into the butter; then roll in crumb mixture and place on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour in a 400° oven.
Do not turn the chicken during baking.
This is a real favorite with my family, because it is so good, and a favorite of mine because it is so simple to do.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Place broccoli in a buttered casserole 1/2 at a time.
Alternate layers of the cheese sauce and crackers with the broccoli.
Save some of the crackers and cheese sauce for a topping.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Mix flour, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix buttermilk and soda.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in preserves, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Cook
rinds
in
salted water until tender; drain well. Cook sugar, vinegar, water and spices.
Add melon rinds.
Cook on low heat until rinds are clear.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix by hand and shape into balls about the size of English walnuts. Press out flat. Press pecan halves on top. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°. Especially good with spiced tea or mulled cider.

title: hamburg and pea casserole
directions: Cook hamburg and drain; add peas, cream of mushroom soup and milk and mix.
Bake 1/2 hour to heat through.
Last few minutes of cooking, add onion rings on top.

title: garden potato chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine vegetables, water, bouillon cube and pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are very tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture to vegetables, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens. Add process cheese spread; heat until process cheese spread is melted and chowder is hot.
Garnish with crisply cooked bacon, crumbled, if desired.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: our family spaghetti(student favorite)
directions: Saute onions in olive oil until translucent.
Add meat and garlic.
Stir until meat is brown.
Drain off excess grease.
Add all other ingredients, except the last 1/2 teaspoon of garlic powder.
Stir and mash tomatoes until mixed.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Add remaining garlic powder.
Cover.
On low heat, cook for another 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and water; add to chicken mixture.
Gently stir in eggs.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and
measure
level
cups,
adding baking powder. Add flour, then
milk,
more
flour and then the sour cream.
Then add
remainder of flour.
Add flavorings, beating after each. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: spinach sensation
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 9-inch deep-dish pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine sour cream, egg yolks, flour and black pepper in large bowl.
Beat egg whites in medium bowl with electric mixer at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Stir one-fourth of egg whites into sour cream mixture; fold in remaining egg whites.

title: cherry nut loaf
directions: Blend margarine with powdered sugar and mix well.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix after each egg.
Add vanilla and then the sifted flour, one cup at a time.
Mix well after each cup.
Add cherries and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef stew with biscuits
directions: Brown stew meat rolled in flour.
Put in saucepan.
Add mixed vegetables and seasoning mix.
When it is done, place in roaster pan.
Mixture needs to be slightly thickened (cornstarch can be added).
Put homemade biscuits or canned biscuits on top.
Place in oven until biscuits are browned.
Serve vegetables over biscuits.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; spread onto graham cracker crust.
Spread pie filling on top.
Chill and serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Roll out and cut into biscuits.
(Do not have to wait to rise.)
Cook at 500°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat ingredients good.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Insert knife in center; if it comes out clean, it's done.

title: party potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs until done. Cool.
Peel potatoes and eggs and chop together.
Add jar of pickle relish after draining excess liquid from pickle relish. Sprinkle to taste with garlic salt and pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Toss or mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered casserole; add topping.

title: pop's apple ugly cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix in bowl the sugar, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in oil, eggs and vanilla.
Batter will be thick.
With hands, mix in apples, raisins and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Leave plain or top with thin layer of frosting.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, cream of tartar, salt and soda.
Roll in small balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Let cool slightly on cookie sheet, then put on cookie racks to cool completely.

title: praline strips
directions: Preheat oven to 400.
Put crackers in an ungreased pan. In sauce pan blend butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Add pecans and spread over cracker.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Cut in strips while warm.

title: dobie
directions: Beat all ingredients together in mixing bowl until well blended.
It will have the appearance of whipped cream.
Store in covered container
in
refrigerator.
Use to grease any pan for baking, such as
cake
layers,
Bundt pans, corn bread and biscuits.
All such products will bake evenly and never stick. Keeps indefinitely.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O
with boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Makes
a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour into dish and mold. Chill; cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: orange french toast
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, sprinkle yeast over the warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon of the honey.
Let stand until soft (about 5 minutes).
Stir in milk, remaining honey, salt and the 2 tablespoons butter.
Add 3 cups flour.
Blend then beat at medium speed until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Stir in about 2 cups more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a board or pastry cloth coated with some of the remaining 1/2 to 1 cup flour.
Knead until dough is smooth and satiny and small bubbles form just under surface (10 to 15 minutes), adding just enough flour to prevent dough from being sticky.
Cover ball of kneaded dough with plastic wrap and a kitchen towel; let rest for 30 minutes.

title: my pepperoni bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat cookie sheet with cooking spray. Unroll dough onto sheet; cover dough with cheese slices, then top with rows of pepperoni slices.
Starting at short end, roll up dough; place, seam side down, on cookie sheet.
Using knife, make 5 (1-inch) slits along top of dough.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes before slicing.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: banana bread(make in a food processor.)
directions: Cut bananas in pieces and put in processor; turn on.
Add shortening, sugar, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add eggs.
Mix for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. I use Pam on the pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: cookie cake
directions: Sift together the flour, cinnamon and soda.
Add sugar and set aside.
Bring to a boil the butter, cocoa and water.
Pour this mixture over the dry ingredients and beat well.
Add the eggs and buttermilk.
Beat well and bake 16 minutes in 350° oven.
Batter will be thin.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 11 x 17 x 3/4-inch cookie sheet or similar shallow pan.
Makes 30 to 35 servings.
Ice with a canned chocolate frosting.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Garnish with cashews right before serving.

title: health cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Sift dry ingredients and add slowly. Add vanilla. Fold in oatmeal, Krispies and pecans. Drop by teaspoon on greased pan. Cook at 325° until crisp.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Dice 1 package of chipped beef very finely and add to cream cheese.
Dice the 2nd package to roll the ball in.
Make one large or two small balls.

title: taters, dogs and eggs
directions: In a large skillet, fry potatoes. When done, add hot dog mixture and then eggs.
Mix slightly and serve.

title: quick unmolded salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In saucepan, boil sliced potatoes until tender.
Put in a buttered 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Make sauce.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and spread evenly in a 9 x 5-inch loaf dish. Microwave 16 to 20 minutes on 60 (Medium) until set in center.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix soup, lemon juice, garlic, salt, pepper, sour cream and mushrooms (if desired) with onions, then fold in rice and shrimp. Pour into a 9 x 11-inch dish.
Sprinkle grated sharp cheese on top. Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.

title: aunt dinny's famous chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add and beat together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, cloves and cocoa.
Stir in 2 cups shredded zucchini.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in 13 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch pan.

title: one egg banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until bread tests done.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Graham cracker crust should cover bottom and 1 1/2-inches up sides of spring-form pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad whip-up
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix together cottage cheese and Cool Whip until well blended.
Mix in jello powder thoroughly.
Add fruit and coconut.
Mix until well blended.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Your kids will love this quick and simple to make treat!

title: brandy alexander
directions: Mix all of the above and enjoy.

title: smiling faces(kids)
directions: Slice peeled oranges crosswise.
Top with peanut butter.

title: crunchy walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out pastry and line a 1 1/2-inch deep 9-inch pie pan.
In a bowl, beat eggs, sugar, corn syrup, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and butter until well blended, then stir in walnuts.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake on lowest rack of oven until filling jiggles only slightly in center when pan is gently shaken (about 50 minutes).
Place on a rack and let cool until slightly warm.
Meanwhile, prepare Hard Sauce, if desired. Top each slice of pie with a dollop of sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruited pork chops
directions: In crock-pot, stir together orange juice, lemon juice, salt and spices.
Trim fat from pork chops.
Place pork chops in juice mixture and top with fruit.
Cook 8 hours on low heat or until pork chops are tender.
Remove chops and fruit to platter.
Keep warm.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into individual dishes or put in large serving bowl.
Chill 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Add onion and green pepper.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar. Add to the vegetables.
Fold in grated cheese.
Crisp fry or broil bacon; crumble into small pieces and fold in, saving a few to sprinkle over top.
Chill well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: salmon stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil over medium-high temperature, stirring constantly.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Grind nuts fine.
Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
In saucepan, combine cream and chocolate squares.
Heat until just melted.
In medium bowl, combine nuts and sugar.
Stir in chocolate mixture and rum.
Turn into pan and refrigerate until firm.
Shape into 30 balls.
Roll in chocolate sprinkles.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, fruit and celery.
Chill. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients except nuts. Chill.
Just before serving, combine chicken mixture, dressing and nuts.

title: souffleed rice casserole
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Lightly butter 1 quart casserole. Melt
butter
over
low heat.
Add onions; saute 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in rice, parsley, egg yolks, milk, cheese, salt and pepper. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold them into rice mixture.
Spoon into buttered casserole.
Place this in a slightly
larger
pan.
Pour in enough hot water to come halfway up
side
of
casserole.
Bake
minutes
or
until slightly puffed and firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Rinse beef and chop fine.
Mix 1/4 cup beef with cream cheese and add remaining ingredients.
Make into ball.
Roll in remaining beef.

title: fig cookies
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Mix sugar and shortening together.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla; add to creamed mixture.
Knead dough until very smooth, about 15 minutes.
Cut dough into 10 pieces.
Roll each piece out to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into strips, about 4-inches wide.
Fill with Fig Filling. Roll up and then cut into any design.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 300° to 325°; they will turn light brown.
Spread on Icing, if desired.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: chicken and shrimp jambalaya
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and brown in bacon fat. Remove from pan.
Sprinkle flour into fat remaining in pan and cook, stirring constantly, until light brown (roux).
Return chicken with sausage, onions, green pepper, tomatoes and garlic to pan and cook, stirring gently, about 10 minutes.
Stir in water, thyme, salt, red pepper sauce and rice.
Simmer 15 minutes; stir in shrimp and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in parsley and green onions and simmer 5 minutes longer or until rice is tender.

title: pizza by yount
directions: Measure water into bowl.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved. Stir in sugar, salt and oil.
Add 2 cups of flour and beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl; brush top with oil. Cover and let rise until doubled (about 30 minutes).
Punch down and divide in half.
Pat out in 2 pizza pans.
Add sauce, favorite toppings and cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes or until crust is brown.
Makes excellent bread sticks, also!

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and cream again.
Add dry presifted ingredients alternately with coffee.
Pour in 3 greased and floured (or Pamed) cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes, or until done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Assemble all ingredients and utensils.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Use jumbo shrimp allowing 3 per person.
Split shrimp through center leaving shell whole.
Remove vein; stuff with the remaining ingredients.
You melt butter; add lobster paste or tamale, garlic and salt, then the crackers.
Stuff shrimp.
Place in broiler pan with a little water (it keeps shrimp from sticking to shell). Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Combine flour, oleo and walnuts; mix well.
Pat mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip over baked and cooled crust. Blend pudding and milk and spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread another cup of Cool Whip over entire mixture and chill before serving.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil in a large saucepan, add noodles and chicken.
Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes until noodles are tender.

title: wheatmeat
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients for 1 minute in blender.
Pour into mixing bowl and add Do-pep.
Stir until mixture forms into a ball.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut with scissors into desired size and drop into 6 cups boiling water.
Cook 1 hour.
Do not remove cover.
Let cool.

title: moist, scrambled eggs
directions: Break eggs in frying pan; add milk, salt and seasoning.
Stir until done.
Top with cheese.
Makes one large serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the sugar, oleo and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and immediately add peanut butter, oats, cocoa and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Melt the first 4 ingredients in a double boiler; cool.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt the oleo in oven.
Add the brown sugar, flour and chopped pecans; mix and spread in pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, stirring every 4 to 5 minutes with a fork until mixture is crumbly.
Remove 1/3 of this mixture for topping; pat the rest in bottom of pan.
Add a 1-inch layer of butter pecan ice cream.
Cover with cooled fudge mixture; top with remaining crumbs. Freeze.
Remove from freezer just before serving.
Serves 16.

title: white sauce mix
directions: Stir flour, salt and dry milk together. Cut in
margarine until you have fine granules.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps 6 weeks.
Makes 1 quart.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into ice cream freezer. Finish filling ice cream freezer with milk and freeze.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and salt.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and let set 15 minutes.
Refrigerate and use within one week.

title: aunt hazel's jello salad
directions: Pour the 2 cups boiling water into bowl with the lemon and lime jello's.
Let set until starts to thicken, then add the cottage cheese and horseradish.
Mix together the salad dressing and the cup of evaporated milk.
Add to the mixture.
Then add the drained crushed pineapple.
Let it set in the refrigerator for a while before serving.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk and cream to scalding; do not boil.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add oysters with liquid.
Cook gently, just until oyster edges curl.
Add to scalded milk and cream.
Season with celery salt.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: egg nog(4 servings)
directions: Note:
If serving children, mix liquor separately and add "nog" to adult servings.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar, salt and corn syrup together 2 minutes on High.
Stir and cook 2 more minutes on High.
Add baking soda and pour over popped corn in grocery bag.
Cook in bag 30 to 40 seconds.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add milk.
Roll coconut, raisins and pecans in flour and add to mixture.
Then add beaten egg yolks. Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff.
Bake in four layers in 350° oven.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, milk and oil; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Mix a few minutes.
Add vanilla and poppy seed; mix until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan, 9 x 5-inch.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: grandmom langebartel's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Mix and add milk slowly.
Add flour and baking powder slowly.
Bake about 1 hour in slow oven.

title: purple cow
directions: Whirl milk, grape juice and 1 cup ice cream in blender at high speed until thick.
Serve in tall glasses, topped with more ice cream.
May be garnished with whipped cream and maraschino cherries.

title: chipped beef dip(single batch)
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature; chop chipped beef into small pieces. Pour salsa into bowl with cream cheese. Add chipped beef and stir. Serve with salty Fritos!

title: sara mauser's sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Blend well.
Shape into 2-inch roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, milk.
Cook until pudding consistency in microwave.
Add egg yolks slowly.
Add vanilla.
If too thick, add a little milk.
If too thin, cook for an extra minute.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of mixer for 3 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together dry ingredients and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured jelly roll pan at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll and allow to cool.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Pour in 9 x 14-inch pan. Cook about 1 hour or until done.
Cool before cutting.

title: dilled ricotta torte
directions: In a bowl, combine bread, almonds and butter.
Press mixture onto the bottom and one-inch up the sides of a well buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into 6-inch ball. Place into crock-pot.
Flatten with hand or spoon so that meat will contour to the crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 to 6 hours.

title: tuna-spinach bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°F.
Cook spinach as directed on package. Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Blend in mayonnaise and lemon juice.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Cook pie filling, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat; add dry jello.
Cool until syrupy.
Add pineapple with juice, nuts and Coke.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In small bowl, combine peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter.
Mix until well blended and chill thoroughly.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts and refrigerate until ready to dip. When ready to dip, melt milk chocolate chips and shortening in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip balls into chocolate, covering completely.
Place on wax paper and chill until set.

title: breakfast in one pan
directions: Brown meat and onions; press rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Seal together and up 1/2 inch on sides of pan.
Mix milk, eggs, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Spread meat mixture on rolls and pour egg mixture over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook and stir water, sugar, salt and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 box strawberry jello.
Add food color.
Cool.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell. Refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: glorified rice
directions: Put in bowl and mix well all together. Can be served with cherry as garnish. Serves 6 to 8.

title: party pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, then whole eggs and brandy.
Add flour last.
Batter will be very thick.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: granny buchan's old fashion tea cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Beat egg and flavoring.
Sift in flour and soda. Roll into 1-inch balls; pat flat.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 7 dozen.

title: easy nachos
directions: Brown ground beef.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan, layer refried beans, then ground meat, salsa and cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with sour cream and avocado slices.
Dip with chips.

title: w.m.u. punch
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and fruit juices.
Pour some of the punch into ice trays and freeze.
When ready to serve, pour the punch over ice cubes in a punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 25 (6 ounce) servings.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Cover beans with 2-inches water. Bring to a boil; boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain and rinse beans well, discarding liquid. In

a large pan, combine the broth, beans, parsley, bay leaves, country ham and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Add the onion, carrot, celery and potato. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until beans are tender. Discard the bay leaves; serve with cornbread.

title: ground beef with eggplant(moussaka)
directions: Leaving the skin on, slice the eggplant into 1/2-inch slices. Sprinkle well with salt and allow to drain for about 20 minutes. Wash off this salt and dry the eggplant on a towel.
Heat the salad oil and fry the slices, a few at a time, until golden brown on both sides.

Slice the peeled and washed potatoes into 1/4-inch slices and fry these in same manner, adding more oil if necessary. Saute the chopped onion and garlic in the 6 tablespoons of butter and add the ground beef.
Brown 10 minutes.
Add the salt, pepper, mint, parsley, cinnamon and tomato paste.
Remove cover and cook another 10 minutes to reduce the liquid.
Arrange half of the eggplant in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish about 4 inches deep.
Top with half of the potatoes and half of the meat.
Repeat this process with the remaining eggplant, potatoes and meat.
Cover evenly with cream sauce.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat well.
Add egg yolks; beat well. Add hot water, then dry ingredients.
Stir in grated potatoes and nuts.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into batter.
Bake at 350° in cake pans.

title: date loaf
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add canned milk.
Add sugar and beat.
Add fruit and nut mixture with crumbs.
Mix together, then fold in the egg whites which have been beaten well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake in slow oven for 40 minutes.

title: stir and drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil, peel and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: ham it up dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix well. Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: roast venison
directions: Wash and trim meat.
Soak overnight in salted water to cover. Drain off water and re-soak in salted water.
Trim off shreds of whitish substance, if any.
Into bottom of a deep baking pan, sprinkle dry onion soup mix.
Set roast into mix sprinkled pan. Combine vinegar, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce and spoon over meat.
Place onion slices on top of meat.
Cut strips of suet and secure to meat with toothpicks.
Cover pan with heavy aluminum foil; seal edges of foil around lip of pan.
Cover loosely to allow space for steam.
Bake 4 hours at 325°.

title: diet pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn down oven to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve in a hollow shell of a round French bread loaf.
Use bread cup from center, cut it up and dip in the dip.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and milk. Combine mixtures only until moistened.
Fold in strawberries. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 10 large muffins.

title: tuna mold
directions: Mix all ingredients except gelatin.
In hot water, dissolve gelatin by adding a little at a time.
Mix gelatin with other ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: rice and chicken casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonstick coating.
Heat broth and butter until melted.
Add all ingredients, except chicken and mix well.
Place chicken on top and cover.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: rice-sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; remove from pan.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
(Drain grease from sausage and blot with paper towels to remove as much grease as possible.)
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg. Sift together and blend in flour and baking soda.
Stir in nuts and morsels.
Drop on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Stir together the flour, salt, baking powder, cream of tartar and sugar.
Cut in the Crisco until the mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add the sour cream and mix a little, then add the milk all at once, stirring until the dough forms a ball.
Roll out on floured surface and knead lightly just until dough holds together nicely.
Roll out to about 3/4 inches thick and cut with floured cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise while oven heats to 400°.
Bake until lightly browned, about 15 minutes. Makes about 1 dozen biscuits.
Serve with Honey Butter or Strawberry Butter.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl. Add other ingredients. Using egg beater, mix well until mixture is foamy. Serve at once.

title: linguini vegetable salad(one serving)
directions: In medium bowl stir together Italian dressing, vinegar and celery flakes.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Toss gently to mix well.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Contains 189 calories.

title: sausage skillet express
directions: Combine sausage, celery and onion in large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: missionary bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves onto sheet of waxed paper.
Bring water to a boil.
Add raisins and sugar and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from the heat.
Add butter, walnuts and dry ingredients.
Mix well and spoon into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Loaf pans may be lined with foil to make it easier to remove from pans.
Foil should also be greased.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Whisk all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add water to desired consistency.

title: great-grandma's lemon cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Combine flour and baking soda; add alternately with milk, stirring well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into two well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to cool completely.
Dust tops with confectioners sugar.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick margarine and 1 egg together and pat into a cake pan.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Beat half and half and pudding mix with wire whisk for 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Freezes well.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the 3 cups of liquid.
Add 1 quart vanilla ice cream, drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp with fettucine
directions: Clean shrimp and coat with salt, pepper and flour and set aside. In a large pan, saut oil, butter, wine and garlic on medium heat. When hot, add shrimp and lemon juice and cook for 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp are pink. Add half and half and onions; stir and let simmer for 10 minutes. Let sauce thicken. Cook fettucine per directions on box; drain and add to shrimp. Mix well and serve.

title: rich pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: tomato pie
directions: Peel and chop coarsely or quarter enough tomatoes to fill an unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with onions and chopped basil, salt and pepper.

title: chocolate dipped bananas
directions: Peel and cut bananas in half crosswise, so that you have 8 pieces. Insert a popsicle stick in the end of each peeled banana. Place bananas on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Place in the freezer, keep then in there as long as possible, at least 10 to 20 minutes. Heat chocolate bits with butter in a double boiler over low heat until the chocolate melts and butter is incorporated. Dip the chilled bananas in chocolate and roll into your favorite topping. Chill or freeze until ready to serve.

title: pickled beets(regular or sugar free)
directions: Drain beets. Cut into bite size pieces. Heat beet juice with rest of
ingredients
to boil. Take off stove.
Pour over beets. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Take 1 roll Ritz crackers and 1 stick margarine. Crumble crackers and melt margarine.
Pour over cracker crumbs (makes crust).
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare in long dish.
Mix Cheez Whiz, margarine and soup together.
Add pimentos and mushrooms.
Add rice and broccoli. Cover dish.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: frozen yogurt pops(children's favorite)
directions: Place ingredients in a large bowl and stir until well blended. Spoon into small paper cups and insert wooden ice cream spoons. (A small piece of foil wrapped around top of cup will hold spoon in place.)

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and cut up artichokes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Soften cream cheese, cream with milk, blend in sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Halve the cake and tear into small bits, layer in pan or oblong casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 of cream mixture over cake.
Make another layer of cake tidbits and cover with remainder of cream mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving spread with cherry pie filling.
Other pie fillings can be used.

title: tangy broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli and place in a serving bowl with onion and bacon.
Toss with mixture of Miracle Whip and vinegar.
Toss in sunflower seeds just before serving.
Best if left to marinate for at least a few hours or all day.

title: baptist cookies
directions: Put dates, sugar, egg and butter in Dutch oven and heat.
Stir until dates melt.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and pecans. Mix well.
Cool.
Roll portions into balls the size of walnuts. Roll in coconut or pecans.

title: chocolate cherry cream pie
directions: Make pudding using directions for pie.
Pour into shell. Chill until firm.
Cover with pie filling, then Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Make 2 layers, then cut into an order to make 4 layers.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Spread between layers.
Refrigerate for 48 hours.
Use 8 ounces Cool Whip and 1 cup coconut to ice the outside.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix together the jello and hot water, stirring until jello is completely dissolved.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Add the cranberry sauce and beat with mixer on low setting until mixture is smooth. Stir in the thawed strawberries with juice and the pineapple with juice.
Pour into a large mold or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: meat-cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature.
Chop beef, mushrooms and onions.
Mix everything.
Shape in 2 balls.
Roll in grated pecans.

title: scallops and linguine
directions: Rinse scallops. Drain. In electric frypan, add butter and garlic. Saute scallops about 5 minutes. Add linguine mix. Ready to serve.

title: chicken and mushrooms dijon
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken with onions for 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove chicken pieces.
Over medium heat, add another tablespoon of margarine and cook the broccoli and mushrooms until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Add soup, milk and mustard.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Serve with noodles.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients together but only use half of the onion rings.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden; about the last 5 minutes, cover with remaining onion rings.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: down south chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook
chicken and debone (save broth).	Melt shortening in boiling
water.
Add beaten egg, salt and flour.
Mix well, using the amount of
flour
needed
until
dough	is
easy
to handle, not sticky.
Cover	with plate for about 30 minutes in refrigerator.

title: ginger chops
directions: Dip pork chops in egg on both sides; cover on both sides with bread crumbs.
Bake on rack at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, turning once.

title: sloppy joe turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and onion.
Drain and add salt, garlic powder, catsup and sour cream.
Mix well on greased cookie sheet; roll each biscuit to a 4 x 4-inch square.
Place 1/4 cup of meat mixture in center of each square.
Fold over corner of squares to form a triangle.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cran-raspberry salad
directions: *Cran-raspberry jelly can be found right in the same area as regular cranberry sauce.

title: southern gumbo
directions: Coat veal cubes well in flour.
Slowly heat butter in 8-quart kettle.
In it, brown veal cubes well, turning on all sides.
Add onion, okra and tomatoes.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add 2 quarts of water and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Makes 5 quarts (20 servings).

title: light chicken and rice gumbo
directions: In large saucepan over medium heat, heat chicken broth, chicken, corn, tomatoes, okra, rice and pepper until mixture comes to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until chicken and rice are cooked.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tandoori chicken breasts(makes 4 servings)
directions: PREPARE CHICKEN AND REFRIGERATE WITH SEASONED PASTE AT LEAST 2 HOURS OR OVERNIGHT!

title: blini
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours.
Have ready a small container of melted butter.
Heat a 10-inch crepe pan.
Brush with the melted butter.
Pour batter, about 1/4 cup at a time; rotate quickly to spread.
Cook over medium heat until bottom is slightly browned and top is set.
Turn out on lightly buttered plate; repeat until batter is used.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Grease pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and pour over cake.
Bake again for 10 minutes.
Let set for 1/2 hour.
Put in refrigerator.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender; dip in cold water.
Peel off skins. Mix ingredients for syrup.
Pour over beets and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.

title: sweet n' tangy chicken and rice
directions: Prepare rice according to pkg. directions.
In an oiled skillet, brown chicken on both sides.
Add vegetables and heat through.
In small bowl, combine honey, mustard and soy sauce. Pour into skillet with chicken and vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over a bed of rice.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: tropical buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add buttermilk, orange rind and melted butter.
Add sugar mixture, blending thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold into buttermilk mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted near the edge of filling comes out clean.

title: tangy meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck with dry dressing and onion.
Form into round balls.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Brown meatballs.
Drain off excess grease.
Add can of beef broth.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice or as a main dish alone.

title: classic bourbon wassail punch
directions: Combine orange peel, cloves, allspice and cinnamon in a piece of cheesecloth.
Tie to form a bag.
Set aside.
Combine apple cider and orange juice in a large Dutch oven.
Add spice bag. Bring mixture to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Discard spice bag.
Add bourbon to cider mixture.
Serve hot. Makes 1 gallon.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
In a smaller bowl, mix together the oil, egg and milk.
Add the liquids to the dry ingredients.
Mix with few strokes.
Add oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Cook the chicken in the water, liquid smoke, turmeric and salt. Cool and cut into chunks.
Add to chicken the almonds, grapes, celery, onions, apples and green peppers.

title: grilled lemon-thyme chicken breasts(low-fat)
directions: Put breasts in a glass baking dish that will hold them in one layer.
Beat the remaining ingredients in a small bowl with a fork and pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 hours.
Turn the breasts over once during that time.
Preheat broiler.
Remove the breasts from marinade and broil 4 minutes each side.
Or grill over charcoal.
Serves 4.
Tastes delicious when served cold on a picnic.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together the packed brown sugar, cornstarch and chili powder.
Stir the tomato sauce, vinegar, catsup and corn syrup into the brown sugar mixture in the saucepan. Add 1/2 cup water.
Bring the mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir the orange liqueur or orange juice into the tomato sauce mixture.
Return to boiling; reduce the heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and egg yolks until well blended (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Pour into graham cracker pie shell; chill until set.
Egg whites can be used for meringue, if desired.

title: italian style lemon chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, in a bowl and set it aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut chicken into serving pieces, wash and dry with paper towel.
Place chicken in a baking pan and cook until about half done.
Spread 1/2 the lemon juice mixture over the chicken and continue cooking until just about finished (10 minutes or so).
Spread the remaining mixture and finish cooking. Be sure to put all the "juice" over the chicken when serving it.

title: quick raspberry pie
directions: Cook jello, cornstarch, sugar and water until thick.
Allow to cool.
Mix in quart of berries.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: chicken country style
directions: Mix 1/2 teaspoon salt with flour and roll chicken in mixture. Melt butter in frying pan and brown the chicken on all sides at high heat.
Peel potatoes and onions.
Scrape and quarter carrots lengthwise.
Slice peppers in 1/2-inch strips.
Mix remaining salt, sugar and pepper with tomatoes.
Place 2/3 of vegetables in bottom of large pan.
Place chicken on top and add remaining vegetables.
Pour tomatoes and 3 cups boiling water over all. Cover tightly and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, except for cheese.
Mix well. Pour 1/2 batter in a hot greased 9 or 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with remaining batter.
Cook at 450° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: s'more pie
directions: Prepare pie crust as directed.
Prepare pudding as directed. Immediately stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with marshmallows. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: italian christmas cookies
directions: Drop cookies, bake at 350° 10-12 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, cream, vanilla, butter, corn syrup, salt, cooking sherry and rum extract in medium bowl.
Beat well with spoon.
Add pecans and mix.
Pour into baked pie shell.
(When baking pie shell, use weights; don't prick the crust.)
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes until set in center.
Use knife to see if comes out clean as with custard.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In a large skillet, saute green pepper and onion in butter. Add remaining ingredients except flour and soy sauce. Simmer until hot.
Make a paste of the flour and soy sauce. Add to ingredients in skillet and stir well.
Continue simmering for approximately 10 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: strawberry angel ribbon loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake batter.
Divide equally between 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 29 to 32 minutes.
Suspend cakes upside down and cool for 30 minutes.
Then split each loaf into 3 layers.
Soften yogurt 20 minutes at room temperature.
Divide in fourths.
Assemble loaf as follows:
bottom cake layer, yogurt spread evenly, middle cake layer, yogurt and cake top.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
Cut into slices.

title: cranberry rose punch(serves 12)
directions: Just before serving, mix wine, cranberry cocktail and sparkling water.
Pour over ice.
Garnish with lemon or orange slices.

title: grilled marinated shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in shallow dish.
Stir well.
Add shrimp, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Combine vinegar, ketchup, sugar and seasonings.
Add meat and simmer until cooked.
Add pineapple.
Heat again and adjust seasoning.
Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti according to package.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella, Parmesan, Italian seasoning, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
In baking dish, spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce.
Put shells on top. Spread remaining spaghetti sauce on top.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella on top.
Bake, covered at 350° for 40 minutes.
(I did not bake this long, just until cheese was melted.)

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add eggs, carrots and vegetable oil.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Add sugar and shortening to hot mashed potatoes.
Mix and add other ingredients. Work well until smooth.
Let stand in covered bowl for about 4 or 5 hours. Roll out fairly thick. Cut into biscuits and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Melt 1 stick (or less) oleo.
Add 3 cups Rice Krispies.
Spread on top.
Brown lightly.

title: grandma's cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wacky cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift first five ingredients into an ungreased 8
x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Make three holes in the sifted layer.
In
the
first
hole,
add the vinegar.
In the second, vanilla extract;
in the third, salad oil.	Pour water over the
whole thing and mix well.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until tester comes out clean.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix the 4 boxes of pudding with milk.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding and bananas in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Repeat 2 times.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: pineapple candy - sugar-free
directions: Drain pineapple juice into pan.
Sprinkle on the gelatin and 1/2 of pineapple.
Wait 1 minute until gelatin softens.
Heat gently until gelatin granules melt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and sugar substitute.
Spread mixture in 8-inch square no-stick pan.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.
Contains 10 calories per square.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in salt; make 2 layers with sauce in between and on top.
Mix other ingredients except almond chips and heat until bubbly for sauce.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle almonds on top the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Slash frankfurters every inch.
Brown frankfurters in shortening.
Add chopped onion and chili powder; cook until onion is tender.
Stir in tomato soup and water; simmer a few minutes. Stir now and then.
Just before serving, add some pickle chips if you like.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
This recipe is great for picnics!

title: spinach surprise
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Fold in onion, lemon juice and cubed cheese. Stir in cheese until completely melted.
Great side dish at holiday time.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cream oleo and 1 1/2 cups sugar together.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy. Stir together dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into walnut size balls, then roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Cookies will puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.

title: appleskeiver
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix egg yolks in bowl. Add buttermilk with melted butter.
Do not whip.
Before you add flour mixture, whip egg whites stiff.
Add flour mix to buttermilk and butter mix, then fold in egg whites.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash in small amount of water until tender; drain well.
Mix all ingredients together except herb dressing. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with herb dressing.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pirogies
directions: Boil potatoes and mash.
Grate cheese and add to potatoes. Let cool.
Prepare the dough.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add eggs.
Mix with hands, adding 2+ cups of water when needed.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Butter side of saucepan, in it combine first 5 ingredients. Cook to hard stage, stir in vanilla.
Slow pour over corn.
Butter hands and shape into balls.

title: orange-pineapple punch
directions: Stir together milk, juice, and soda.
Top with sherbet.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in bananas. Add flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Makes 2 small loaves.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and refrigerate to chill before serving.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Coat a large Dutch oven with cooking spray; add cabbage and remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
6 servings; 54 calories per 1 cup serving.

title: stuffed macaroni
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Boil macaroni; let cool and then stuff with meat.
Place in a baking dish; sprinkle with cheese and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 20 minute chocolate cake
directions: In saucepan, mix oleo, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and flour, mixing well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 12 x 15-inch cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: roast and gravy
directions: Season both sides of roast with Tony's seasoning; brown in iron skillet that has been sprayed with Pam. Put soups over roast; add enough water to cover roast. Cook uncovered in oven for 4 hours at 350°. Remove meat and slice. Place slices back into gravy.

title: fresh pork sausage strata
directions: Saute and crumble pork sausage.
Brush both sides of bread with melted butter.
Layer bottom of 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan with six slices of the bread.
Sprinkle sausage pieces over bread.
Lay one slice of cheese on each piece of bread.
Set the remaining 6 slices of trimmed bread over the bottom slices.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: 1st Layer: Melt margarine. Combine first 3 ingredients; press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Cool completely.

title: forever fresh cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Wash and cut rhubarb.
Add sugar; let stand for a few minutes. Heat slowly and simmer gently until rhubarb is tender but still keeps its shape.
Soften gelatin in cold water; add to hot rhubarb.
Heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Add few drops of red coloring, if desired.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Add nuts, celery and lemon juice.
Pour into molds.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs in a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in lightly greased pie plate at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out on a cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake, then allow to cool.
Top with a mixture of cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread strawberry glaze on top of cream cheese layer. Top with sliced fruit.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts.

title: bread dough
directions: Cook and mash potatoes; add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and eggs.
Add butter/margarine and milk which has been scalded; mix thoroughly. Dissolve yeast in water and 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar mixture.
Add to potato mixture.
Add 2 cups flour; beat well.
Use a dough hook if available and add remaining 6 to 7 cups flour.

title: good pound cake
directions: Mix together with mixer 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can bake in loaf pans, just reduce baking time.

title: "john wayne" eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 300° until set (about 20 minutes).
Knife inserted 1-inch from edge of pan should come out clean.
If desired, substitute 1/4 cup chopped jalapeno peppers for green chilies and onion.
Spray pan with Pam.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Add in large container Kool-Aid and sugar with about 1/2 gallon water.
Have frozen juices thawed and add along with rest of water.
Add ginger ale last.
A frozen ring can be added in punch bowl.
This punch is good made ahead and refrigerated.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat and season with salt and pepper and chopped onions.
Drain grease.
Roll ground meat and grated cheese in flour tortilla.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine enchilada sauce and soup.
Pour over pan of enchiladas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through, about 30 minutes.
Garnish with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: company sicilian supper
directions: Brown beef; add onion and cook until tender.
Drain fat.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In another pan, heat milk and add cream cheese.
Blend well.
Add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, garlic salt and drained noodles.

title: curry and dill shrimp sauce
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Combine 6 quarts water, 1/2 cup salt, dill and cut up lemon.
Boil 5 minutes, then add shrimp.
Boil 4 minutes, turn off heat and let soak 20 minutes.
Drain and remove lemon.
Cut bottom off of artichokes; boil for 20 minutes. Remove, drain and let cool.
Mince onion, garlic, celery and parsley to make a paste (a mini chopper works well for this). Slice the mushrooms and saute them with the paste in 2 tablespoons olive oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Set aside.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a
9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: blueberry corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 12-muffin tin with butter. Combine the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. In another bowl, combine the egg, buttermilk and oil, then blend with wire whisk.
Pour the egg mixture into the dry ingredients, stirring until blended.
Fold the blueberries into the batter.
Be careful not to overmix or the batter will turn blue.
Spoon the batter into greased muffin tin.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve the muffins warm with butter.

title: ma ma darling's "chicken in a hurry"
directions: Cut
into
serving
pieces
or	other
selected pieces. Season to taste.
To seasoned chicken, add onion, tomato sauce and mustard.
Saturate	well and transfer to appropriate size baking dish
or
slow cooker.
If cooking in oven, bake, covered, 30
to 45	minutes
at
If	in slow cooker, cook according to instructions.

title: boy's twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until almost done.
Remove from oven long enough to cool, then peel.
Set aside.
In a large pot or mixing bowl, add margarine to potatoes while warm.
Add margarine, milk and sour cream.
Beat well until blended.
Add chives, bacon bits and 1/2 package cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Put into large baking pan or dish.
Add remaining shredded Cheddar on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 heaping helpings.

title: brunch dish
directions: Mix well together the 2 1/4 cups milk, eggs and dry mustard. Layer half of the first 3 ingredients with half of the egg mixture. Repeat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, mix the soup with the 1/2 cup milk.
Mix well and pour over top.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: different apple pie(servings:  6)
directions: Put chopped or grated apples in mixing bowl and add sugar, egg, margarine and spices.
Pour in unbaked shell and bake 1 hour at 375° or until firm and lightly brown on top.

title: queen's sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and nutmeg in medium mixer bowl; add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Place pastry-lined pie plate on oven rack; pour in filling.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes longer.
Makes 1 pie.

title: crunchy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and noodles. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper. Refrigerate.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, baking soda and salt in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine banana, oil, honey, eggs and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Coat a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with cooking spray.
Spoon batter into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield:
1 loaf (about 118 calories per 1/2-inch slice).

title: betty's pineapple surprise
directions: Place can of milk, unopened, in a large pan.
Cover with water; keep at a boil for 3 1/2 hours, never allowing the water to go below the can.
Cool in refrigerator.
(Can boil more than one can at a time and store unused.)
Open both ends of can and gently push out caramelized milk.
Lay on side and slice one slice at a time, using a sharp knife.
Arrange pineapple slices on 6 dessert plates and place caramel slice on top, lining up both pieces as they will be same size.
Top with whipping cream, almonds and cherry.
Very refreshing dessert!

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together all ingredients with an electric mixer. Chill dough for about 2 hours. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 - 10 minutes or until a golden color.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and add club soda. Mix well. Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious chicken spread
directions: Combine minced chicken, crumbled bacon and diced apples with salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Makes 1 cup.

title: kraut
directions: Wash and drain cabbage.
Then shred and pack in a quart jar. Put 1 hot banana pepper in center for hot kraut.
Bring water, salt, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over kraut.
Seal.
Ready to eat in one week.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, cheese and 3/4 stick butter or margarine.
Melt 1/4 stick butter or margarine and add 1/4 cup crackers; mix well.
Save for topping.
Layer broccoli, crackers, cheese and water chestnuts in casserole dish.
Top with buttered crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken with vegetables
directions: In wok, heat 2 tablespoons peanut oil and stir-fry chicken until opaque.
Remove and put into a bowl.
Stir-fry vegetables, garlic and ginger along with mushrooms and green onion for 1 minute.
Add broth with cornstarch until mixture thickens.
Add chicken and toss together.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except peas, in crock-pot on high heat for about 3 hours, then on low heat for 2 to 3 hours. Add package of frozen peas about an hour before stew is done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw the frozen spinach.
Squeeze until dry.
Stir together spinach and remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Cover. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Serve with Bugles.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in blender and pour over vegetables. Marinate in refrigerator.

title: pears and ribs hawaiian
directions: Drain 1/2 cup syrup from canned pears for marinade. Refrigerate pears.
Cut spareribs into 2-rib portions.
Combine reserved 1/2 cup pear syrup with vinegar, corn syrup and salt. Pour over ribs and marinate overnight.
Drain, reserving marinade. Broil ribs 6-inches below broiler unit 15 to 20 minutes on each side, basting frequently with mixture of 1/2 cup pear marinade, molasses and soy sauce.
Add pear halves to pan the last 10 minutes, basting with sauce during the last 5 minutes.
Brush pears and ribs with pineapple preserves to glaze.
Makes 6 servings.

title: paul's bacon and potato pie
directions: Grease	a
x
13-inch baking dish.
In a frying pan, brown the
bacon until crisp.
Drain and blot on paper towel. Combine the
bacon	and
remaining	ingredients.
Spread
the mixture evenly
in	the prepared baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes; cut into squares.
